{"type":"message","id":"11da1555","parentId":"2b639208","timestamp":"2026-04-13T04:28:21.147Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The log shows:\n1. The v8 version (pid 11100) started on port 8080 - that's wrong, it should be 3104\n2. Then a new process tried to start on 8080 and failed (EADDRINUSE)\n3. The final message \"Loaded embedding classifier... Pipeline initialized... Scene Classifier API v2.0 starting on port 8080\" - this seems to be from a 3rd process (pid 11366)\n\nWait - looking at it again:\n- \"Started server process [11100]\" + \"Uvicorn running on http://0.0.0.0:8080\" - this was from the earlier run (pid 11100)\n\n\n- \"Started server process [11411]\" + \"ERROR: [Errno 98]... 8080\" - this is a newer attempt that failed because 8080 was already taken\n- Then the final lines show another process loading the embedding classifier and initializing on 8080\n\nSo it looks like pid 11366 actually started successfully on 3104, but the logs aren't showing the startup message for it. Let me reconsider what's happening here. The log file seems to capture multiple runs, and I need to figure out which process actually succeeded and which ones failed.\n\nLooking at the log output more carefully - it shows two startup attempts. The first one succeeded on 8080, the second one failed on 8080 because the port was already in use. But I'm seeing 3104 in the ss output and a 500 error, which suggests something else is going on. I think I'm looking at logs from multiple processes that got mixed together. Let me just restart fresh and see what actually happens.\n\nWait - I should check the working directory of pid 11366 first to understand what's actually running.","thinkingSignature":"f726d7916c80cfcdd72666cc8220363253875f04b7171183dfa9e5e0276d93d3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bcf0c847fe6d490686c7edab","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /proc/11366/cmdline | tr '\\0' ' '; echo; readlink /proc/11366/cwd"}}],"api":"anthropic