{"type":"message","id":"d13cb362","parentId":"709c71ee","timestamp":"2026-04-13T04:28:29.734Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So pid 11366 is the v8 version (cwd is /home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier), and it has already started on port 3104. But the /tmp/scene-classifier.log shows it also says \"Scene Classifier API v2.0 starting on port 8080\" which doesn't match. Something is mixed up in the logs.\n\nActually I think there are TWO processes both started on 3104:\n- pid 11366 is the v8 version that grabbed 3104\n- pid 11100 is the workspace version that grabbed 8080\n\nBut both show up as \"pt_main_thread\" in lsof... which is odd.\n\n\nThe issue is that both the v8 and workspace versions have the same code structure, so when the v8 version tries to load the workspace module path, it's importing from the same source and creating this conflict where both instances are trying to bind to the same ports.\n\nLooking at the logs more carefully, the workspace version is running on 8080 while the v8 version is on 3104, but the 3104 request is returning 500 errors. I need to check if there's a process priority or initialization order issue causing the classifier to fail even when the server is up.\n\nLet me trace through what the v8 api_server.py is actually doing when it receives that 3104 request.","thinkingSignature":"b65077e2465c91cae2b72dc7b2329c5608ac2e3a630098602146448945c1af73"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c445815921034ad4b880ad41","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier/api_server.py | grep -A 30 '@app.post'"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":140,"output":331,"cacheRead":44288,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44759,"cost":{"input":0.000042,"output":0.0003972,"cacheRead":0.0026572799999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0030964799999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776054501234,"responseId":"062ba3e5629f49054ebd7689d8063649"}}
{"type":"message","id":"586c5f7b","parentId":"d13cb362","timestamp":"2026-04-13T04:28:29.817Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_c445815921034ad4b880ad41","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"@app.post(\"/classify\")\ndef classify(req: ClassifyRequest):\n    # 检查熔断器\n    now = time.time()\n    if circuit_breaker[\"is_open\"]:\n        if now - circuit_breaker[\"last_failure\"] > circuit_breaker[\"timeout\"]:\n            # 尝试恢复\n            circuit_breaker[\"is_open\"] = False\n            circuit_breaker[\"failures\"] = 0\n            print(\"Circuit breaker: attempting recovery\")\n        else:\n            # 直接使用规则分类器\n            result = rule_classifier.predict(req.text)\n            result[\"meta\"] = \"circuit_open_fallback\"\n            return result\n    \n    if not pipeline:\n        # 管道未初始化，使用规则分类器\n        result = rule_classifier.predict(req.text)\n        result[\"meta\"] = \"pipeline_unavailable\"\n        return result\n    \n    try:\n        result = pipeline.process(req.text, req.context)\n        # 成功，重置熔断器\n        circuit_breaker[\"failures\"] = 0\n        return result\n    except Exception as e:\n        # 失败，增加计数\n        circuit_breaker[\"failures\"] += 1\n        circuit_breaker[\"last_failure\"] = now\n--\n@app.post(\"/feedback\")\ndef submit_feedback(req: FeedbackRequest):\n    if not feedback:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=\"Feedback not initialized\")\n    \n    return {\"status\": \"recorded\"}\n\n@app.get(\"/stats\")\ndef get_stats():\n    return {\"message\": \"Check logs/meta_events.jsonl\"}\n\n# ========== 热更新端点 ==========\n@app.post(\"/reload-rules\")\ndef reload_rules():\n    global rule_classifier\n    try:\n        # 确保配置目录存在\n        os.makedirs(CONFIG_DIR, exist_ok=True)\n        \n        # 如果存在覆盖规则文件，加载它\n        if os.path.exists(RULES_FILE):\n            with open(RULES_FILE, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                rule_overrides = json.load(f)\n            # 重新初始化规则分类器\n            rule_classifier = RuleClassifier(custom_rules=rule_overrides)\n            return {\n                \"status\": \"reloaded\",\n                \"rules_file\": RULES_FILE,\n                \"rules_count\": len(rule_overrides) if isinstance(rule_overrides, dict) else 0\n            }\n        else:\n            return {\n                \"status\": \"no_override\",\n                \"message\": \"No rule_overrides.json found\"\n            }\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=f\"Reload failed: {str(e)}\")\n\n@app.post(\"/update-rules\")\ndef update_rules(rules: dict):\n    \"\"\"动态更新规则\"\"\"\n    try:\n        os.makedirs(CONFIG_DIR, exist_ok=True)\n        with open(RULES_FILE, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n            json.dump(rules, f, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)\n        # 触发重载\n        return reload_rules()\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=f\"Update failed: {str(e)}\")\n\n@app.get(\"/rules\")\ndef get_rules():\n    \"\"\"获取当前规则\"\"\"\n    if os.path.exists(RULES_FILE):\n        with open(RULES_FILE, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n            return json.load(f)\n    return {\"message\": \"No custom rules\"}\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    print(\"Scene Classifier API v2.0 starting on port 3104...\")\n    uvicorn.run(app, host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=3104)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":57,"aggregated":"@app.post(\"/classify\")\ndef classify(req: ClassifyRequest):\n    # 检查熔断器\n    now = time.time()\n    if circuit_breaker[\"is_open\"]:\n        if now - circuit_breaker[\"last_failure\"] > circuit_breaker[\"timeout\"]:\n            # 尝试恢复\n            circuit_breaker[\"is_open\"] = False\n            circuit_breaker[\"failures\"] = 0\n            print(\"Circuit breaker: attempting recovery\")\n        else:\n            # 直接使用规则分类器\n            result = rule_classifier.predict(req.text)\n            result[\"meta\"] = \"circuit_open_fallback\"\n            return result\n    \n    if not pipeline:\n        # 管道未初始化，使用规则分类器\n        result = rule_classifier.predict(req.text)\n        result[\"meta\"] = \"pipeline_unavailable\"\n        return result\n    \n    try:\n        result = pipeline.process(req.text, req.context)\n        # 成功，重置熔断器\n        circuit_breaker[\"failures\"] = 0\n        return result\n    except Exception as e:\n        # 失败，增加计数\n        circuit_breaker[\"failures\"] += 1\n        circuit_breaker[\"last_failure\"] = now\n--\n@app.post(\"/feedback\")\ndef submit_feedback(req: FeedbackRequest):\n    if not feedback:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=\"Feedback not initialized\")\n    \n    return {\"status\": \"recorded\"}\n\n@app.get(\"/stats\")\ndef get_stats():\n    return {\"message\": \"Check logs/meta_events.jsonl\"}\n\n# ========== 热更新端点 ==========\n@app.post(\"/reload-rules\")\ndef reload_rules():\n    global rule_classifier\n    try:\n        # 确保配置目录存在\n        os.makedirs(CONFIG_DIR, exist_ok=True)\n        \n        # 如果存在覆盖规则文件，加载它\n        if os.path.exists(RULES_FILE):\n            with open(RULES_FILE, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                rule_overrides = json.load(f)\n            # 重新初始化规则分类器\n            rule_classifier = RuleClassifier(custom_rules=rule_overrides)\n            return {\n                \"status\": \"reloaded\",\n                \"rules_file\": RULES_FILE,\n                \"rules_count\": len(rule_overrides) if isinstance(rule_overrides, dict) else 0\n            }\n        else:\n            return {\n                \"status\": \"no_override\",\n                \"message\": \"No rule_overrides.json found\"\n            }\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=f\"Reload failed: {str(e)}\")\n\n@app.post(\"/update-rules\")\ndef update_rules(rules: dict):\n    \"\"\"动态更新规则\"\"\"\n    try:\n        os.makedirs(CONFIG_DIR, exist_ok=True)\n        with open(RULES_FILE, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n            json.dump(rules, f, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)\n        # 触发重载\n        return reload_rules()\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=f\"Update failed: {str(e)}\")\n\n@app.get(\"/rules\")\ndef get_rules():\n    \"\"\"获取当前规则\"\"\"\n    if os.path.exists(RULES_FILE):\n        with open(RULES_FILE, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n            return json.load(f)\n    return {\"message\": \"No custom rules\"}\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    print(\"Scene Classifier API v2.0 starting on port 3104...\")\n    uvicorn.run(app, host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=3104)","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776054509809}}
{"type":"message","id":"405d8961","parentId":"586c5f7b","timestamp":"2026-04-13T04:28:40.627Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API server code shows it's supposed to run on port 3104, but the log shows \"starting on port 8080\". This is inconsistent. Let me check if there's some kind of environment variable or config overriding the port.\n\nAlso, both pid 11100 and 11366 are python3 api_server.py processes. The one on 8080 is pid 11100 (workspace version), and the one on 3104 is pid 11366 (v8 version).\n\nThe v8 version's log says \"starting on port 3104\" but then why is it running on 8080? Wait, the log for 8080 was from the workspace version's startup. But the workspace version should also use 3104...\n\n\nLooking at the workspace version's api_server.py, it's hardcoded to 8080, so that's the culprit. But the v8 version running on 3104 should be correct based on its code. Yet the v8 version is failing with an Internal Server Error, which suggests the pipeline might not be initializing properly despite the log claiming it's ready.\n\nI need to trace through the pipeline initialization more carefully. Both versions share the same PipelineOrchestrator import from the workspace skill, so if there's an issue there, it would affect both. The fact that one instance starts on 8080 and the other on 3104 but both fail suggests a shared dependency problem rather than a port conflict.\n\nLet me check the PipelineOrchestrator class itself to see what could be causing the initialization failure.","thinkingSignature":"ae2b6d5c4b7e6af81557e38e2d79b349e7ca9256a573f5cd05669939e3272e15"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4577ade4f6d84eeba61c105b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/skills/scene-classifier/pipeline/orchestrator.py 2>/dev/null | head -50"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":814,"output":364,"cacheRead":44416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45