{"type":"message","id":"2613a8cf","parentId":"1a3c1cd5","timestamp":"2026-04-13T04:30:21.019Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The workspace skill's log file is empty (no output). The 3104 service is responding but returns 500. Let me look at what's actually running as pid 12148 - it's the v8 version (python3.8, cwd is /home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier).\n\nWait - the PID changed from 11366 to 12148 after I killed 11366 and started the workspace version. Let me verify which version is actually running on 3104.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully:\n- I ran `/tmp/run_classifier.sh` which starts workspace version\n- The log shows uvicorn on 8080, but 3104 is listening (pid 12148)\n\nSomething is confusing here. The workspace version's api_server.py should run on 3104 (as per the `if __name__ == \"__main__\": uvicorn.run(app, host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=3104)`), but the log shows 8080.\n\nWait - the log file `/tmp/sc.log` shows \"Uvicorn running on http://0.0.0.0:8080\" which means the script I ran might be running a DIFFERERNT version of the api_server.py than expected.\n\nLet me check - maybe there's a different api_server.py being invoked.\n\nActually wait - looking at the log output again:\n```\nINFO:     Started server process [12208]\nINFO:     Waiting for application startup.\nINFO:     Application startup complete.\nINFO:     Uvicorn running on http://0.0.0.0:8080 (Press CTRL+C to quit)\n```\n\nThis looks like it's the workspace version trying to start on 8080 (the default in the @app decorator), not 3104. But the __main__ block should override to 3104...\n \nThe workspace version is importing from the same pipeline.orchestrator and FeedbackCollector modules as the v8 version, so they should both be trying to bind to the same port. But I'm seeing 8080 in the log instead of 3104, which suggests either the __main__ block isn't being reached or the import is pulling from a different location than expected.\n\nLooking 