{"type":"message","id":"02f0a118","parentId":"48b517b0","timestamp":"2026-04-13T04:39:16.356Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, 3104 IS now occupied by pid 15569. But the log still shows EADDRINUSE. Let me check the log again - the log was written BEFORE the process got the port. There might be TWO processes running now.\n\nActually looking at the output - the log shows an older run's output (from PID 15302). The new run (PID 15569) got the port successfully. Let me verify by checking the current state:\n\n- 15569 is listening on 3104\n- 15598 is another instance\n\nWait, the issue is there are TWO instances running. PID 15569 got 3104, and PID 15598 is the old one from before (from the pre-edit code that had port 8080). \n\nBut the log file is shared, so the newer process probably just overwrote it. Let me check if the 3104 endpoint is actually responding now.","thinkingSignature":"5139efd840d2353b6c90e3b3dabf5573352244ed5bd3640315fe7dc820d62245"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_33345c9055084abea7936fe9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3104/classify -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"帮我写一个备份脚本\"}' 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":239,"output":253,"cacheRead":55936,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56428,"cost":{"input":0.0000717,"output":0.0003036,"cacheRead":0.0033561599999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0037314599999999994}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776055148256,"responseId":"062ba66cbeb2736cce56f06aee6edf26"}}
