{"type":"message","id":"5b9f70b7","parentId":"3dfe94fa","timestamp":"2026-04-13T04:39:54.473Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the systemd services. The ws-proxy.service is configured with:\n- OPENCLAW_WS_URL=ws://localhost:3103\n- PROXY_WS_PORT=3107\n- HEALTH_PORT=3104\n\nSo ws-proxy listens on port 3107 and uses 3103 as the gateway. But wait - HEALTH_PORT=3104 conflicts with our scene-classifier! And ws-proxy is supposed to connect to gateway, which is on 3102, not 3103!\n\nLet me think about what ws-proxy actually does. It's a WebSocket proxy that connects to the gateway. Looking at the config:\n- OPENCLAW_WS_URL=ws://localhost:3103 - this should be ws://localhost:3102 (gateway)\n\n\n- HEALTH_PORT=3104 - this is wrong, 3104 is scene-classifier\n\nAnd the openclaw-router service has:\n- OPENCLAW_GATEWAY=http://127.0.0.1:18789 - but gateway is on 3102, not 18789!\n\nThese service configs are completely misconfigured. I should focus on fixing the dotenv and port issues in the actual code rather than wrestling with systemd services. Let me restart the router and see what happens.","thinkingSignature":"b4793d2db73834b5d5de4bf57b9e27725a4e054c13843cc1b5a565a95a884123"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ecd9a5c2730b4258a6f4deb5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/ai/openclaw-router && node openclaw-router.js > /tmp/router.log 2>&1 &\necho \"PID: $!\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":442,"output":310,"cacheRead":57088,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57840,"cost":{"input":0.0001326,"output":0.000372,"cacheRead":0.0034252799999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00392988}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776055187227,"responseId":"062ba692ebe746d944bc937c23c8434f"}}
