{"type":"message","id":"28bd5702","parentId":"8cad4c1b","timestamp":"2026-04-13T04:46:03.844Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking how I plan to fix the 3103 scorer issue. The problem is that gateway sends `text` field but 3103 expects `prompt` field. I need to look at the v8 scorer API to understand the expected format, then figure out where the mismatch happens - is it in the gateway hook configuration or in the 3103 adapter.\n\nLet me think about this:\n\n1. 3103's SKILL.md says:\n```json\n{\n  \"prompt\": \"<用户消息文本>\",\n  \"context\": { ... }\n}\n```\n\nSo 3103 expects `prompt`, not `text`.\n\n2. The context.json shows scoring with `score: 0` - which means the gateway hook sent a request to 3103 but got a zero score because it was using `text` instead of `prompt`.\n\n3. The gateway has hooks configured for auto-score-classify. The hook is what sends requests to 3103/3104.\n\nSo the fix could be in one of two places:\n- Option A: Fix the gateway hook to send `prompt` instead of `text` to 3103\n- Option B: Fix the 3103 scorer to accept `text` as an alias for `prompt`\n\nOption B is more robust (backwards compatible), but Option A might be more correct if the 3103 API contract says `prompt`.\n\nLet me check the 3103 scorer adapter to see how it handles the incoming request. The skill says it calls `http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score` with `{\"prompt\": \"...\", \"context\": {...}}`. If the gateway is sending `text` instead, that's a hook configuration issue.\n\nBut actually, I should check the actual scoring endpoint code to see if it accepts both fields, or just `prompt`. If it only accepts `prompt`, then the fix is either:\n1. Change the gateway hook to send `prompt`\n2. Change 3103 to accept `text` as well\n\nLet me look at the 3103 scoring code to understand how it parses the incoming request.","thinkingSignature":"bde47db8817b55b6404e3f1aaa16c427160f308d2cd1103ce3e070122e2f432f"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n先查 3103 的实际请求解析逻辑：\n\n| 字段 | SKILL.md 定义 | context.json 结果 |\n|------|--------------|------------------|\n| `prompt` | ✅ 正确 | — |\n| `text` | ❌ 不支持 | score: 0（走了默认值） |\n\n问题是 **3103 期望 `prompt`，gateway 发的是 `text`**。\n\n---\n\n**两个修复方案：**\n\n**方案 A：改 3103 scorer 兼容 `text` 字段（更稳健）**\n- 改动小，向后兼容\n- 任何调用方用 `text` 都能正常工作\n\n**方案 B：改 gateway hook 发 `prompt` 字段（更符合规范）**\n- 更正确，但如果其他调用方也用 `text` 会继续出问题\n\n---\n\n**我的建议：方案 A**——在 3103 的 adapter 层加个兼容：\n\n```javascript\n// 大概逻辑：如果没有 prompt 字段但有 text 字段，用 text\nif (!body.prompt && body.text) {\n  body.prompt = body.text;\n}\n```\n\n这样 gateway 的 hook 配置不用动，3103 自己也更健壮。\n\n---\n\n要修的话我现在就动手。需要确认一下 3103 的 adapter 代码位置：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_441ea3ff9ed34b1da2103fea","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/v8/src/scoring/"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":275,"output":722,"cacheRead":61504,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62501,"cost":{"input":0.0000825,"output":0.0008663999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0036902399999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00463914}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776055549890,"responseId":"062ba7fd0d2c4c1fc5969a7f86a1ae7d"}}
