{"type":"message","id":"39c03308","parentId":"dc0e92be","timestamp":"2026-04-13T04:48:19.961Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the gateway has `auto-score-classify` hook enabled. But the scoring is still showing 0. This could mean:1. The hook is registered but the call to 3103 is failing silently\n2. The hook writes to context.json but the code has a bug\n3. The scoring result is written but the gateway's context.json is not being updated properlyLet me check if the gateway is calling 3103. The fact that classification (3104) is working means the hook itself is running. But scoring might be failing for a different reason.\n\nWait - actually, I need to think about this more carefully. The classification field has been updating (0.565 → 0.698) which means the 3104 call IS happening. But scoring shows 0.\n\nLet me check the gateway's hook implementation to see how it calls 3103.","thinkingSignature":"48d9083f9907c19df7de392e87baec98c7e417b128d1bfac4dc01e567da6c30a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a47b78a4142049b9a87f03a2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw -name \"*.js\" -o -name \"*.ts\" 2>/dev/null | xargs grep -l 'auto-score-classify\\|autoScoreClassify' 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":436,"output":250,"cacheRead":66176,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66862,"cost":{"input":0.00013079999999999998,"output":0.0003,"cacheRead":0.00397056,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00440136}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776055693468,"responseId":"062ba88d213b0c89b4022a1c7ae09913"}}
