{"type":"message","id":"8e4836bb","parentId":"8ba3f26d","timestamp":"2026-04-13T04:48:26.783Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_8b05dd6a43e948f1b563d67f","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"// auto-score-classify hook\n// Concurrent classification (3104) + scoring (3103) on every inbound message\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\nasync function fetchJSON(url, body, timeoutMs = 3000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData) },\n      },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n          try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); }\n          catch { resolve(null); }\n        });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n    req.setTimeout(timeoutMs, () => { req.destroy(); resolve(null); });\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n    setTimeout(() => { try { req.destroy(); } catch {} }, timeoutMs);\n  });\n}\n\nasync function runClassification(text) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3104/classify\", { text }, 3000);\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\", { prompt }, 3000);\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n    fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n  }\n}\n\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const text = event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\";\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) return;\n\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || \"default\";\n  const sessionDir = path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw/sessions\", sessionKey);\n  ensureDir(sessionDir);\n\n  const [classification, scoring] = await Promise.allSettled(["}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":55,"aggregated":"// auto-score-classify hook\n// Concurrent classification (3104) + scoring (3103) on every inbound message\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\nasync function fetchJSON(url, body, timeoutMs = 3000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData) },\n      },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n          try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); }\n          catch { resolve(null); }\n        });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n    req.setTimeout(timeoutMs, () => { req.destroy(); resolve(null); });\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n    setTimeout(() => { try { req.destroy(); } catch {} }, timeoutMs);\n  });\n}\n\nasync function runClassification(text) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3104/classify\", { text }, 3000);\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\", { prompt }, 3000);\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n    fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n  }\n}\n\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const text = event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\";\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) return;\n\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || \"default\";\n  const sessionDir = path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw/sessions\", sessionKey);\n  ensureDir(sessionDir);\n\n  const [classification, scoring] = await Promise.allSettled([","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776055706769}}
{"type":"message","id":"cd8028fa","parentId":"8e4836bb","timestamp":"2026-04-13T04:48:34.716Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the hook handler. It calls 3103 with `{ prompt }` (not `text`), and 3104 with `{ text }`. \n\nLooking at the handler:\n```javascript\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\", { prompt }, 3000);\n}\n```\n\nAnd:\n```javascript\nasync function runClassification(text) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3104/classify\", { text }, 3000);\n}\n```\n\nSo the hook sends:\n- 3104: `{ text }` ✅ (3104 expects `text` - I verified this works)\n- 3103: `{ prompt }` ✅ (3103 expects `prompt` - my fix also handles `text` for robustness)\n\nBut the context.json shows scoring is all zeros. Let me look at the rest of the handler to see how it writes to context.json.","thinkingSignature":"496dd977573fae399b171a38f0762f7e4c7dabfc680a04dcb4759834cd58eff8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_93412947037d4d8fbbc91daa","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js | sed -n '60,120p'"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":541,"output":251,"cacheRead":66688,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67480,"cost":{"input":0.0001623,"output":0.0003012,"cacheRead":0.004001279999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00446478}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776055706786,"responseId":"062ba8997c6d7c9d5b5772fa99c15c47"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8153779a","parentId":"cd8028fa","timestamp":"2026-04-13T04:48:34.802Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_93412947037d4d8fbbc91daa","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"const [classification, scoring] = await Promise.allSettled([\n    runClassification(text),\n    runScoring(text),\n  ]);\n\n  const result = {\n    classification: classification.status === \"fulfilled\" ? classification.value : null,\n    scoring: scoring.status === \"fulfilled\" ? scoring.value : null,\n    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n    messagePreview: text.slice(0, 120),\n  };\n\n  const outPath = path.join(sessionDir, \"context.json\");\n  try {\n    fs.writeFileSync(outPath, JSON.stringify(result, null, 2), \"utf-8\");\n  } catch {\n    // ignore write errors silently\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":51,"aggregated":"const [classification, scoring] = await Promise.allSettled([\n    runClassification(text),\n    runScoring(text),\n  ]);\n\n  const result = {\n    classification: classification.status === \"fulfilled\" ? classification.value : null,\n    scoring: scoring.status === \"fulfilled\" ? scoring.value : null,\n    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n    messagePreview: text.slice(0, 120),\n  };\n\n  const outPath = path.join(sessionDir, \"context.json\");\n  try {\n    fs.writeFileSync(outPath, JSON.stringify(result, null, 2), \"utf-8\");\n  } catch {\n    // ignore write errors silently\n  }\n}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776055714788}}
{"type":"message","id":"8bda219a","parentId":"8153779a","timestamp":"2026-04-13T04:49:01.765Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full picture. The hook calls:\n- `runScoring(text)` which sends `{ prompt: text }` to 3103\n- But the gateway might not be calling this hook at all\n\nWait, looking at the hook more carefully - it calls `runScoring(text)` which sends `{ prompt: text }`. So it DOES use `prompt` field, not `text`. \n\nBut the context.json shows `scoring: null` or zero values. This means the hook either:\n1. Isn't being triggered at all\n2. Is failing silently\n\nLet me check if the hook is actually being called. The hook checks `event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\"`. So it only runs on \"preprocessed\" messages.\n\n\nThe classification field has been updating with new values over time, which suggests the hook is at least partially working, but the scoring stays at zero. Looking at the actual data, the classification response seems malformed - it's showing a JSON stringified version of what should be a structured object, and the scene value appears incomplete or corrupted.\n\nThe real issue is that the hook writes `{ classification, scoring }` directly to context.json, but something's going wrong with how the classification object is being serialized or stored. The gateway might be writing to context.json independently, and there could be a conflict between what the hook writes and what the gateway expects - particularly around the field naming mismatch where the hook uses `scene` but something else might be expecting `label`.\n\nLooking at the hook's write logic, it's doing a direct `JSON.stringify(result)` to the file, so if the hook was running properly, the classification field should reflect what was actually returned. The fact that it shows `\"[LLM\\u54cd\\u5e94]\"` suggests the hook might be processing responses but hitting a serialization issue or writing corrupted data.\n\nThe scoring field being zero or empty points to either the hook not executing for this particular message, the HTTP request to port 3103 failing, or the response not being written back to context.json properly. Since the classification is updating with different confidence values (0.565 → 0.698), the hook is definitely running—but something's breaking the score calculation or storage.\n\nLooking at the timing, the last message at 12:45 triggered the hook, but the current context.json might be from an earlier interaction before the 3103 fix took effect. The real question is whether the hook's Promise.allSettled is actually resolving the scoring request correctly, or if it's silently failing without updating the score field. The hook does write a `classification` field, and the context.json shows one with a response field and scene value, which suggests something is writing to it. But the hook is also supposed to write `scoring`, and that's showing null or zero. Let me check if maybe there's a second hook or process that's overwriting the context.json without the scoring data. Since the classification has been updating (0.565 → 0.698), the hook is clearly running, but something's preventing the scoring from being captured properly. The hook writes to `context.json` but `sessionDir` is constructed from `event.sessionKey`. Looking at the current context, the session key appears to be `agent:main:main`, so the path would be `~/.openclaw/sessions/agent:main:main/context.json`. But I'm seeing `classification` and `scoring` fields there—though `scoring` is all zeros while `classification` has actual values, which suggests the hook is running but the scoring data isn't being populated correctly.\n\nWait, I should check whether there are actually two different context.json files being written to. The gateway might write to one location while the hook writes to another. Let me trace where the gateway actually persists its context to see if these are separate files or if something's overwriting the scoring field after the hook writes it.\n\nThe hook itself looks fine - it's sending text to both 3104 and 3103, and the context structure matches what the hook produces. So either the hook is being bypassed for certain messages, or something's resetting the scoring values after the hook runs. Since this is the main session with direct webchat access, the gateway should be routing through the hook system properly, but there might be a fallback mechanism that's overwriting the context with default values when the hook doesn't run.\n\nThe fact that classification is updating (0.565 → 0.698) proves the hook executed at least once, but the scoring staying at zero across multiple messages suggests the 3103 service might not be returning valid data. I should test whether 3103 is actually responding correctly when the hook calls it. The scoring object shows all factors as zero with a total of 0, which means it's not the default structure and was actually computed - but with a total score of 0, suggesting the `prompt` field in the request was empty or the scoring service returned nothing useful.\n\nThe issue is likely that `event.context?.bodyForAgent` is empty when the hook runs, causing `runScoring(\"\")` to execute with an empty string, which then scores as 0 across all factors since there's no actual prompt text to evaluate. The context.json keeps getting overwritten with the latest data, so earlier entries should reflect what was actually returned from the API at that time. The hook sends `text` to the scoring endpoint, which expects `prompt` instead - that mismatch might explain the zero scores. Let me test the 3103 API directly to see what's actually being returned.\n\nLooking at the context.json timestamps, the most recent entry is from 04:44, which was after I fixed the adapter to handle the `text` field properly. So the fix should be working, but the scoring still shows all zeros. The issue is that the hook itself constructs `{ prompt: text }`, which is correct - but maybe the fix I made isn't being picked up by the running service, or there's a mismatch between what the hook sends and what the API is actually processing.\n\nLet me verify the fix is actually in place and test the endpoint directly to see what's happening.","thinkingSignature":"087409fa57a37f693e2744b83899aa1ca387ef8362fde7780dc58850c7435d25"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHook 代码找到了。发的是 `{ prompt: text }`，字段名是对的。但 scoring 一直是 0，说明 hook 发过去但 3103 返回了异常值。\n\n让我直接测 hook 走的路径：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3759bd1052d44600b6aa7bf0","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3103/api/score -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"prompt\":\"帮我写一个备份脚本\"}' 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":226,"output":1357,"cacheRead":67200,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68783,"cost":{"input":0.0000678,"output":0.0016284,"cacheRead":0.004032,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0057282}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776055714804,"responseId":"062ba8a29f0e0fc5b9eb506982a4ce12"}}
