{"type":"message","id":"323949df","parentId":"1adc69dc","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:02:13.373Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's a lot in memory! The cron jobs are configured and the memory infrastructure is solid. Let me check if there's a skill that was installed for periodic memory updates. Also let me check the cron to see if there's a \"dream\" or \"memory dreaming\" job mentioned in the earlier context.\n\nEarlier in the memory file, I saw:\n- Cron: memory-maintain ✅ 每天3点\n- Cron: memory-keeper ✅ 每天4点\n- Cron: Memory Dreaming Promotion ✅ 每天3点\n\nSo there's a \"Memory Dreaming Promotion\" cron. Let me check what that is.\n\nAlso the crontab we set has both memory_keeper (4h) and memory_maintain (3h). The \"Memory Dreaming Promotion\" was mentioned in the earlier gap analysis but it's not in the current crontab. Maybe it was an old plan that didn't get implemented.\n\nLet me check if there's a \"dream\" script.","thinkingSignature":"de6303f94a14c3df84a3254aa1e28915a7b09b30f97fa97a56508ba92c4b380e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_052f5ca8db8c402b993fcb50","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/ | grep -i 'dream\\|promot\\|ingest'"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":79275,"output":237,"cacheRead":1152,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80664,"cost":{"input":0.023782499999999998,"output":0.0002844,"cacheRead":0.00006911999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.024136019999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776056522193,"responseId":"062babc9c42c382df38db202ae3f5620"}}
