{"type":"message","id":"365b4708","parentId":"71dce592","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:12:03.477Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-04-13 13:11 GMT+8] 不用每条信息都写入啊，之写入关键信息"}],"timestamp":1776057123465}}
{"type":"message","id":"c254a3d3","parentId":"365b4708","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:12:24.666Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is clarifying that the system doesn't need to write every message - just key information. This is a much more reasonable approach. Let me think about how to implement this.\n\nKey information would include:\n- User explicitly saying \"记住...\" (remember...)\n- Important decisions made\n- Lessons learned (\"以后都用X不要用Y\")\n- Project state changes\n- User preferences expressed\n- Errors fixed / bugs resolved\n\nThe existing `memory_keeper.sh` already has some of this logic:\n```bash\ngrep -i \"记住\\|学会\\|偏好\\|规则\\|喜欢\\|讨厌\\|以后都\\|要使用\\|用.*不要\" \"$session_file\"\n```\n\nSo the approach would be:\n\n\n1. During conversation, when key info is identified, write to `memory/ephemeral/`\n2. Or have a cron job that periodically scans recent session and extracts key info\n3. memory_keeper handles consolidation\n\nThe tricky part is figuring out when something is actually key information. The user could explicitly say \"记住X\", but there's also implicit signal - like when a decision gets made or a problem gets solved, I could recognize that and write it down proactively. The simplest path forward is probably having a hook or periodic scan that runs through recent messages and pulls out the important stuff.\n\nFor the periodic scan approach, I already have the grep patterns in memory_keeper.sh that look for \"记住\", \"学会\", \"偏好\", and similar keywords - these would catch explicit memory requests. The cron runs daily, but I could set up something more frequent to capture ephemeral notes between sessions.\n\nThe real issue is that this session has been mostly framework fixes - not much worth remembering in terms of user preferences or decisions. I should be more intentional about asking the user what matters to them, or I could run a quick session scan to identify what was actually important from this conversation.","thinkingSignature":"da7350b58de90a31fd6fb74c3b2ed013275860a4c576b3b6093f7fb1943e66cc"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n对，这才是正确的设计。\n\n**关键信息就几种**：\n\n| 类型 | 触发信号 |\n|------|---------|\n| 用户明确说\"记住…\" | `记住.*` |\n| 决策结论 | `决定用.*` / `最终方案是.*` |\n| 教训/踩坑 | `以后.*不要.*` / `别用.*用.*` |\n| 偏好 | `喜欢.*` / `用.*不要.*` |\n| 进度 | `完成了.*` / `还在做.*` |\n\n现有 `memory_keeper.sh` 已经有这个提取逻辑，只是没配高频 cron。\n\n---\n\n**最简单的实现**：\n\n1. 写一个轻量脚本，扫描当前 session 文件，找出关键信息\n2. 每小时跑一次，写到 `memory/ephemeral/`\n3. `memory_keeper.sh` 每天合并 ephemeral 到主记忆\n\n或者更简单——**在对话过程中随时写入**。当你说\"记住…\"或者做了重要决策，我直接写文件，不需要等 cron。\n\n---\n\n**现在要不要做这个**？可以在这次 session 结束前，把这次修框架的关键结论先写进 memory/，算是验证一下记忆链路。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":84682,"output":620,"cacheRead":1152,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86454,"cost":{"input":0.0254046,"output":0.000744,"cacheRead":0.00006911999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02621772}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776057123488,"responseId":"062bae22cb6d95d9b1f43f924bc8520c"}}
