{"type":"message","id":"3e84a57e","parentId":"7e6040fd","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:13:33.606Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-04-13 13:13 GMT+8] 关键信息设计是不是太少了？使用元会不会更好"}],"timestamp":1776057213597}}
{"type":"message","id":"2395f937","parentId":"3e84a57e","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:13:55.182Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking whether using metadata (instead of keyword-based detection) might be better for identifying key information. They're right - metadata (like intent signals, classification results, scoring) could be a better way to determine what's important than just keyword matching.\n\nLet me think about this:\n\nCurrent approach (keyword):\n- \"记住...\" / \"决定用...\" / \"以后不要...\"\n- Problem: misses things that aren't explicitly marked, relies on user saying specific phrases\n\nMetadata approach:\n- classification result (e.g., `task_multi_step` = probably important task)\n- scoring result (high score = complex/important task)\n- `intercepted: true` (high risk operation = important to remember)\n- session type / agent type\n\nThis is actually a much better signal! The v8 engine already produces these:\n- classification: scene label + confidence\n- scoring: score + factors + strategy\n\nHigh score (e.g., MEGA_TASK) = complex multi-step work = worth remembering\nHigh risk intercepted = safety decision made = worth remembering\nExpert user scene = deep discussion = might be worth remembering\n\nThe user is right - using the metadata from the classification/scoring system is more systematic than keyword matching. It's already being generated for every message!\n","thinkingSignature":"ddf47a02f868df62500c87a5ed7ec0b02ecda21f506e0e01807cdf9063d20d16"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n对，metadata 更好。\n\n**keyword 的问题**：依赖人说\"记住...\"，但关键信息往往没有明显标记。\n\n**metadata 的优势**：每条消息都有现成的信号，不需要猜。\n\n```\nclassification.scene = \"task_multi_step\"  → 多步骤任务，重要\nclassification.scene = \"fault_recovery\"    → 故障处理，重要\nclassification.intercepted = true         → 高风险拦截，重要\nscoring.score >= 60                       → 复杂任务，重要\nscoring.recommendedStrategy = \"SPAWN_SUBAGENT\" → 需要子代理，重要\nscoring.recommendedStrategy = \"MEGA_TASK\" → 巨型任务，必须记住\n```\n\n**这套系统在这次 session 里已经跑着了**，而且分类/评分结果已经写入了 context.json。\n\n问题是：这些 metadata 只存了，没被用来驱动记忆写入。\n\n---\n\n**更好的设计**：\n\n```\n每条消息 → 3104 分类 + 3103 评分\n        ↓\n当 score >= 某个阈值（如 50）或 intercepted == true\n        ↓\n自动写一条到 memory/ephemeral/\n        ↓\nmemory_keeper.sh 每天合并到主记忆\n```\n\n这样不需要关键字，不需要用户说\"记住\"，系统自动判断哪些该记。\n\n要实现吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":84931,"output":517,"cacheRead":1216,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86664,"cost":{"input":0.0254793,"output":0.0006204,"cacheRead":0.00007295999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02617266}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776057213620,"responseId":"062bae7d115aea9632fc30f0646a33c9"}}
