{"type":"message","id":"cbe87d6a","parentId":"668d8e12","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:18:15.361Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking what to do now given the harsh assessment. The core issues are:\n\n1. context.json is written but never read\n2. No real-time capture (only on /new)\n3. memory_keeper.sh extracts low-quality raw text, not structured insights\n\nThe most important fixes are:\n1. Make context.json be read somewhere (hook or bootstrap)\n2. Add real-time capture capability\n\nBut wait - the user asked me to think strictly. Let me think about what's actually actionable right now that would make the biggest difference with the least amount of work.\n\nOption A: Fix context.json reading - but I don't know what should read it. Bootstrap reads session-summary, not context.json. The auto-score-classify hook writes it.\n\n\nOption B: Add a simple real-time capture trigger in the existing hooks - when important signals appear (intercepted, MEGA_TASK, etc.), write to ephemeral immediately.\n\nOption C: Write the key conclusions from this session to memory now as a test/validation.\n\nOption D: Implement a lightweight version of the metadata-driven capture I designed earlier.\n\nLet me think about what's actually doable quickly:\n\nOption C is trivial - I can write the key conclusions from this framework repair session to memory right now. This would at least validate the write path.\n\nOption B is more valuable but requires modifying the existing hook which might be complex.\n\nThe most pragmatic next step is to capture the key insights from this session while they're fresh - the framework repairs, the scoring classifier fix, the cron setup - and write them to memory. That validates the write mechanism and gives the memory layer something concrete to work with. Then I can assess whether the real-time capture problem is actually solvable given the constraints.","thinkingSignature":"49bc358c701e9283799deea8519df4cb597016f9a81d8bef761ac72a9b68c2d8"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n## 下一步\n\n**两件事可以立刻做：**\n\n---\n\n**1. 先把这次修框架的结论写进 memory/（5分钟）**\n\n这次 session 的关键决策和结论：\n- 3104 classifier 修好了（numpy序列化）\n- 3103 scorer 修好了（text字段兼容）\n- openclaw-router 是半成品，disable 了\n- cron 重新配了5条有效任务\n- 记忆系统评审：总分 3/10，大部分时间是死的\n\n写进去之后，下次 session 可以验证 bootstrap 是否读到。\n\n---\n\n**2. 解决 context.json 从未被读取的问题**\n\n这是最浪费的部分。需要搞清楚：**谁应该读 context.json？**\n\n- auto-score-classify hook 只负责写\n- bootstrap 读的是 session-summary（另一个文件）\n\n如果我让 bootstrap 在启动时也读 context.json 的 classification/scoring 信息注入到 session，就能利用每条消息的 metadata。\n\n---\n\n**先做哪件？**\n\n1. 写这次结论进 memory（验证记忆写入路径）\n2. 研究 context.json 是否可以让 bootstrap 读（更根本的修复）\n\n还是两件都做？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":86480,"output":580,"cacheRead":1216,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88276,"cost":{"input":0.025944,"output":0.000696,"cacheRead":0.00007295999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.026712959999999997}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776057480211,"responseId":"062baf87abdf9f889c29f99e5014ef11"}}
