{"type":"message","id":"cd4da900","parentId":"b2246030","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:32:31.743Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about borrowing from \"LLM entity pages\" - these are the wiki entities in memory/ that were mentioned earlier. Let me think about what they are.\n\nFrom the memory directory listing:\n- memory/entities\n- memory/knowledge/\n- memory/knowledge.md\n\nThe LLM Wiki entities are structured pages generated by wiki-auto-learn.py. They contain structured information about entities, concepts, etc. \n\nThe user is suggesting: when processing a message that triggers the \"meaningful\" condition, instead of just writing a raw metadata fragment to ephemeral/, we could look at the LLM entity pages and see if this topic relates to existing entities, then write a structured entry that references/updates those entities.\n \nThis is actually a solid idea. Rather than creating isolated fragments, I could write directly to the entity pages in memory/knowledge/, which would keep the memory system properly organized. When a message gets classified as task_multi_step or fault_recovery, I could look up related entities and either create a new one or update an existing one. The wiki-auto-learn.py script that already does this kind of structured ingestion could be leveraged here.\n\nThe workflow would be: meaningful message triggers → query existing entities for related topics → write or update entity pages with the new information. The entities would capture what was decided, what failed, and current status with timestamps and source references.\n\nThis approach keeps memory/entities/ as the permanent source of truth, ephemeral/ becomes unnecessary, and session-summary just needs to verify all entities are current and nothing critical got missed. It's more sophisticated than simple ephemeral writes, but entities are the natural structure for this kind of knowledge management in the first place.","thinkingSignature":"972378b3b3bcbbd2d20e48267178bb42d1da9d2e69c89970bbc9ab33b154847d"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n对，这是关键洞察。\n\n**LLM entity pages 已经是结构化的记忆单元**：\n\n```\nmemory/entities/\n  openclaw-framework.md    # 框架状态、版本、配置\n  scene-classifier.md      # 模型、端口、状态\n  v8-scorer.md             # 端口、评分规则\n  project-xxx.md           # 具体项目进度\n```\n\n**直接复用这个结构**：\n\n```\n有意义消息触发\n    ↓\n检查是否涉及已知 entity\n    ↓\n有 → 更新 entity 页（追加决策/状态变化）\n无 → 创建新 entity\n    ↓\nsession-summary 验证 entity 完整性\n```\n\n---\n\n**好处**：\n\n| 好处 | 说明 |\n|------|------|\n| 不是碎片 | 写进结构化 page，不是 ephemeral 垃圾 |\n| 不用等 /new | 实时写入，每次都有记忆 |\n| session-summary 压力小 | 只需检查 entity 完整性，不需要提炼 |\n| 可追溯 | 每个 entity 有 timestamp + source |\n\n---\n\n**写入格式**（entity page 追加）：\n\n```markdown\n## 更新 [timestamp]\n\n**消息**: {messagePreview}\n**分类**: {scene}\n**评分**: score={score}\n\n**结论/决策**: {LLM生成一句话}\n**影响**: 涉及 {related_entities}\n\n---\n```\n\n---\n\n**实现路径**：\n\n1. hook 检测有意义消息\n2. 解析消息主题 → 匹配或创建 entity\n3. 写 memory/entities/{topic}.md\n4. session-summary 只需验证 entity 页的完整性\n\n**比 ephemeral → session-summary 提炼 → 合并 少一步，而且更精准。**\n\n---\n\n**要实现吗？**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":606,"output":683,"cacheRead":91200,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92489,"cost":{"input":0.0001818,"output":0.0008196,"cacheRead":0.0054719999999999994,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.006473399999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776058335081,"responseId":"062bb2def645e055fbf7cc1007371918"}}
