{"type":"message","id":"517f131e","parentId":"1e21ec7b","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:39:05.493Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to implement the solution. Let me start with the minimal viable version: hook → ephemeral write (layer 1), and session-summary can be added later.\n\nLet me implement:\n1. First, modify auto-score-classify hook to write to ephemeral/\n2. Then verify it works\n3. Then update session-summary to read ephemeral and do LLM refining\n\nLet me start with the hook modification.","thinkingSignature":"d75a5d6c90db7b7e21748354b67acf70e632de369362685406aadfe4dad9435d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8fced237d01e40eca8c2a18e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":94461,"output":122,"cacheRead":1216,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95799,"cost":{"input":0.0283383,"output":0.00014639999999999998,"cacheRead":0.00007295999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.028557660000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776058721522,"responseId":"062bb4616db5af425dd2d31e0c439bbc"}}
{"type":"message","id":"50588f14","parentId":"517f131e","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:39:05.601Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_8fced237d01e40eca8c2a18e","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"// auto-score-classify hook\n// Concurrent classification (3104) + scoring (3103) on every inbound message\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\nasync function fetchJSON(url, body, timeoutMs = 3000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData) },\n      },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n          try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); }\n          catch { resolve(null); }\n        });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n    req.setTimeout(timeoutMs, () => { req.destroy(); resolve(null); });\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n    setTimeout(() => { try { req.destroy(); } catch {} }, timeoutMs);\n  });\n}\n\nasync function runClassification(text) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3104/classify\", { text }, 3000);\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\", { prompt }, 3000);\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n    fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n  }\n}\n\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const text = event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\";\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) return;\n\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || \"default\";\n  const sessionDir = path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw/sessions\", sessionKey);\n  ensureDir(sessionDir);\n\n  const [classification, scoring] = await Promise.allSettled([\n    runClassification(text),\n    runScoring(text),\n  ]);\n\n  const result = {\n    classification: classification.status === \"fulfilled\" ? classification.value : null,\n    scoring: scoring.status === \"fulfilled\" ? scoring.value : null,\n    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n    messagePreview: text.slice(0, 120),\n  };\n\n  const outPath = path.join(sessionDir, \"context.json\");\n  try {\n    fs.writeFileSync(outPath, JSON.stringify(result, null, 2), \"utf-8\");\n  } catch {\n    // ignore write errors silently\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":73,"aggregated":"// auto-score-classify hook\n// Concurrent classification (3104) + scoring (3103) on every inbound message\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\nasync function fetchJSON(url, body, timeoutMs = 3000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData) },\n      },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n          try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); }\n          catch { resolve(null); }\n        });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n    req.setTimeout(timeoutMs, () => { req.destroy(); resolve(null); });\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n    setTimeout(() => { try { req.destroy(); } catch {} }, timeoutMs);\n  });\n}\n\nasync function runClassification(text) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3104/classify\", { text }, 3000);\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\", { prompt }, 3000);\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n    fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n  }\n}\n\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const text = event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\";\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) return;\n\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || \"default\";\n  const sessionDir = path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw/sessions\", sessionKey);\n  ensureDir(sessionDir);\n\n  const [classification, scoring] = await Promise.allSettled([\n    runClassification(text),\n    runScoring(text),\n  ]);\n\n  const result = {\n    classification: classification.status === \"fulfilled\" ? classification.value : null,\n    scoring: scoring.status === \"fulfilled\" ? scoring.value : null,\n    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n    messagePreview: text.slice(0, 120),\n  };\n\n  const outPath = path.join(sessionDir, \"context.json\");\n  try {\n    fs.writeFileSync(outPath, JSON.stringify(result, null, 2), \"utf-8\");\n  } catch {\n    // ignore write errors silently\n  }\n}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776058745590}}
{"type":"message","id":"427358e1","parentId":"50588f14","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:39:26.614Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to understand what we need to add to this handler:1. **isMeaningful check** - determine if the message should be written to ephemeral/\n2. **Write to ephemeral/** - write metadata to memory/ephemeral/YYYY-MM-DD-HH.jsonl\n\nLet me plan the changes:1. Add EPHEMERAL_DIR constant\n2. Add isMeaningful function with the simplified conditions\n3. After writing context.json, also check isMeaningful and write to ephemeral if needed\n\nThe ephemeral format is JSONL (one JSON object per line).\n\nLet me also think about the EPHEMERAL_DIR - it should be `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ephemeral/`\n\n\nI'll set up the EPHEMERAL_DIR path using the workspace directory from the environment or defaulting to HOME, then ensure the directory exists and write JSONL files with ISO timestamps and meaningful metadata including text preview, classification, and scoring data. I need to set up the ephemeral directory at `memory/ephemeral/` and then define the significance criteria—checking for explicit user intent like \"记住\" or \"决定用\", system-level importance flags, high risk factors, or critical scoring outcomes.\n\nFor scoring, I'll keep it strict and only flag MEGA_TASK as truly meaningful, excluding SPAWN_SUBAGENT since it happens too frequently. I'm also being more inclusive with keyword patterns like \"这个要记\" or \"记下来\" to catch additional signals. The text field should capture the full message since LLM summarization needs the complete context, and I'll add the message timestamp from the event to the ephemeral entry. I'm checking the event structure to see if it provides timing information, but it doesn't seem to include a timestamp field in the context object. I'll use the current time when writing to ephemeral since that's the most accurate option available. Now I'm ready to write out the modified handler.","thinkingSignature":"9b5b1bac69eed91bb9d8554e91babf50c12654297d5a719d4e0c1531758ccc92"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n先读现有 handler，再改：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0c522fea52a645048ebe3d6b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ephemeral/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"dir not exists\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":95096,"output":441,"cacheRead":1216,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96753,"cost":{"input":0.0285288,"output":0.0005292,"cacheRead":0.00007295999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02913096}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776058745606,"responseId":"062bb479e74b15b41ac9121b581d6e62"}}
