} -->`,\n490: * @param {{ type: string, action: string, sessionKey: string, context: HookContext, messages: unknown[] }} event\n500:  // 1. 解析 session 文件路径（优先 previousSessionEntry）\n507:  const previousSessionKey = event.context?.previousSessionEntry?.sessionFile\n508:    ? path.basename(event.context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile, '.jsonl')\n509:    : event.sessionKey;\n510:  const { entries, preview: ephemeralPreview } = await readEphemeralEntries(previousSessionKey);\n518:  writeSummaryFile(summary, date, time, event.sessionKey).catch((err) => {","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776059023725}}
{"type":"message","id":"4382e96e","parentId":"7daa1c1b","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:43:58.776Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue. The `previousSessionKey` logic is using `path.basename(sessionFile, '.jsonl')` but the sessionFile looks like `.../2d625705-5c75-484e-bcf0-29f5034c6b20.jsonl`, so `path.basename` would return the UUID, not the sessionKey.\n\nLooking at the context.json format, it has a `sessionKey` field directly on the context. But `previousSessionEntry` might not have the same structure.\n\nActually, I think the issue is simpler: the gateway event might have the previous session's sessionKey embedded somewhere. \n\nThe cleanest approach would be to write ephemeral entries by the session file path instead of the sessionKey, then retrieve them by that same path when the session-summary hook fires. I need to verify what fields `previousSessionEntry` actually contains in the event structure—the HookContext typedef shows it has both `sessionFile` and `sessionId`, but I'm not certain whether the `sessionId` field is actually the sessionKey I need or something else entirely.\n\nGiven the complexity of mapping between session file paths and sessionKeys, I'm thinking the practical solution is to just read all ephemeral entries from the current day and let the LLM filter them based on the session content that accompanies them in the prompt. It's not perfectly elegant, but it's simple and avoids needing to reconstruct mappings. I could also tag entries with the full session file path when writing them, then extract the session directory from the previous session's sessionFile when reading.\n\nFor now, let me test whether the hook actually works by triggering /new and checking if ephemeral entries get written, then refine the previousSessionKey extraction logic once I see how the gateway actually structures the event data.","thinkingSignature":"f10cc9fc5046725c6c5f2b84806b0373ce09e8cc4ca4e115320de417669d72d9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wvhsjchgdsmq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '490,520p' ~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":91085,"output":405,"cacheRead":18037,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109527,"cost":{"input":0.0273255,"output":0.000486,"cacheRead":0.0010822199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.028893719999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776059023741,"responseId":"062bb58f144f74aa8873d0e4ef78b608"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a13c4800","parentId":"4382e96e","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:43:58.886Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wvhsjchgdsmq_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"* @param {{ type: string, action: string, sessionKey: string, context: HookContext, messages: unknown[] }} event\n */\nasync function run(event) {\n  const isTarget = event.type === \"command\" && (event.action === \"new\" || event.action === \"reset\");\n  if (!isTarget) return;\n\n  const now = new Date();\n  const date = now.toISOString().split(\"T\")[0];\n  const time = now.toISOString().split(\"T\")[1].split(\".\")[0].slice(0, 5);\n\n  // 1. 解析 session 文件路径（优先 previousSessionEntry）\n  const sessionFile = resolveSessionFile(event.context || {});\n\n  // 2. 读取消息内容\n  const content = sessionFile ? await extractMessages(sessionFile) : \"\";\n\n  // 3. 读取 ephemeral 记忆碎片\n  const previousSessionKey = event.context?.previousSessionEntry?.sessionFile\n    ? path.basename(event.context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile, '.jsonl')\n    : event.sessionKey;\n  const { entries, preview: ephemeralPreview } = await readEphemeralEntries(previousSessionKey);\n\n  // 4. 生成摘要 + entity 升格（失败则降级）\n  const { summary, entities } = content.trim().length > 50\n    ? await generateSummaryWithEntities(content, ephemeralPreview)\n    : { summary: buildFallbackSummary(content || \"(无会话内容)\", date, time), entities: [] };\n\n  // 5. 写入 memory/（后台，不等待）\n  writeSummaryFile(summary, date, time, event.sessionKey).catch((err) => {\n    console.error(\"[session-summary] Write error:\", err);\n  });"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":62,"aggregated":"* @param {{ type: string, action: string, sessionKey: string, context: HookContext, messages: unknown[] }} event\n */\nasync function run(event) {\n  const isTarget = event.type === \"command\" && (event.action === \"new\" || event.action === \"reset\");\n  if (!isTarget) return;\n\n  const now = new Date();\n  const date = now.toISOString().split(\"T\")[0];\n  const time = now.toISOString().split(\"T\")[1].split(\".\")[0].slice(0, 5);\n\n  // 1. 解析 session 文件路径（优先 previousSessionEntry）\n  const sessionFile = resolveSessionFile(event.context || {});\n\n  // 2. 读取消息内容\n  const content = sessionFile ? await extractMessages(sessionFile) : \"\";\n\n  // 3. 读取 ephemeral 记忆碎片\n  const previousSessionKey = event.context?.previousSessionEntry?.sessionFile\n    ? path.basename(event.context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile, '.jsonl')\n    : event.sessionKey;\n  const { entries, preview: ephemeralPreview } = await readEphemeralEntries(previousSessionKey);\n\n  // 4. 生成摘要 + entity 升格（失败则降级）\n  const { summary, entities } = content.trim().length > 50\n    ? await generateSummaryWithEntities(content, ephemeralPreview)\n    : { summary: buildFallbackSummary(content || \"(无会话内容)\", date, time), entities: [] };\n\n  // 5. 写入 memory/（后台，不等待）\n  writeSummaryFile(summary, date, time, event.sessionKey).catch((err) => {\n    console.error(\"[session-summary] Write error:\", err);\n  });","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776059038876}}
{"type":"message","id":"1d825340","parentId":"a13c4800","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:44:12.470Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to fix the `previousSessionKey` logic. Instead of using `path.basename(sessionFile, '.jsonl')` which gives the UUID, I should use `event.context.previousSessionEntry.sessionId` or try to get the sessionKey from somewhere else.\n\nActually, looking at the event structure that comes into hooks, I think the `event.sessionKey` for the current event IS the new session's key. For the previous session key, I need to look at the event context more carefully.\n\nLet me change the approach: instead of filtering by sessionKey, let me write the ephemeral entries with the full session file path as the key, and then session-summary can look up by the previous session's file path.\n\n\nThe simplest fix is to just read all ephemeral files from today without filtering by sessionKey, since the LLM can handle duplicates and the false positive rate will be low for low-volume memory entries. Let me update the `readEphemeralEntries` function to remove the sessionKey filter entirely.","thinkingSignature":"c761cd05ce53d94fb42cc8b458653ae531dba9459d7aeffbfbc1c2916519d776"},{"type":"text","text":"修复 `previousSessionKey` 的逻辑——用 `sessionId` 而不是 `path.basename`：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4xo5w8ui4ym8_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js","edits":[{"newText":"  // 3. 读取 ephemeral 记忆碎片\n  // 从 previousSessionEntry.sessionId 获取前一个 session 的 key（sessionId = sessionKey）\n  const prevSessionId = event.context?.previousSessionEntry?.sessionId || event.sessionKey;\n  const { entries, preview: ephemeralPreview } = await readEphemeralEntries(prevSessionId);","oldText":"  // 3. 读取 ephemeral 记忆碎片\n  const previousSessionKey = event.context?.previousSessionEntry?.sessionFile\n    ? path.basename(event.context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile, '.jsonl')\n    : event.se