{"type":"message","id":"b8812f8f","parentId":"ed2cf7eb","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:50:31.648Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking why I'm not using the new ephemeral writing capability I just implemented. They want to see the new two-layer memory system actually working - writing to ephemeral/ in real-time as messages come in, rather than manually writing files.\n\nBut the issue is: the ephemeral writing was just added to the auto-score-classify hook. This session has been going on since before the hook was modified, and the messages in this session were processed by the OLD version of the hook (before my edits). \n\nNow that the hook code has been updated, NEW messages from this point forward SHOULD trigger ephemeral writes. But the user seems to be asking: why didn't the hook automatically write the key decisions we made during this session to ephemeral/?\n\n\nI need to verify whether the ephemeral directory is actually being written to as new messages arrive.","thinkingSignature":"426dc11ce89d857da6ce4cf12021e38bb3bbf604f6fcee78eeb0cec3ea7210f1"},{"type":"text","text":"对的，新 hook 已经部署了，但这次 session 的大部分内容是在改 hook 之前发生的。\n\n现在发一条消息触发它：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e3u2o27ez2hl_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ephemeral/ 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":236,"cacheRead":110646,"cacheWrite":2414,"totalTokens":113350,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.0002832,"cacheRead":0.00663876,"cacheWrite":0.00090525,"total":0.00784341}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776059416263,"responseId":"062bb715662b09bed7082fdd2dc2435a"}}
