{"type":"message","id":"8f60a6b3","parentId":"1a4f43ca","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:50:48.655Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The 13:46 timestamp file is the one I manually created with the test data. The current hour is 13, so a new file should be created at `2026-04-13-13.jsonl` if a new message comes in and triggers the hook.\n\nWait, the current system hour is 13 (GMT+8), but the manual test wrote to `2026-04-13-05.jsonl` which is hour 5. And I manually copied the test data into `2026-04-13-13.jsonl`.\n\nThe issue is that the system clock seems to be showing different hours. Let me check the actual current time.\n\nActually, looking at the timestamps:\n\n\n- I wrote the ephemeral test at 13:40 (Beijing time) → hour 13 → `2026-04-13-05.jsonl` (UTC hour 5)\n- The manual copy into `2026-04-13-13.jsonl` was at 13:46 (Beijing time) → hour 13\n\nSo the hook would write to hour 13 UTC... which corresponds to 21:00 Beijing time. But the system shows the current hour as 13 (Beijing time). This is confusing. Let me check the actual current time.\n\nActually, looking at the files more carefully: `2026-04-13-05.jsonl` at 13:40 Beijing time (UTC+8) = 05:40 UTC, and `2026-04-13-13.jsonl` was manually created. When a new message arrives, the hook should write to the current hour's file using `new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 13).replace('T', '-')` which would give `2026-04-13-13` in UTC.\n\nWait, the Beijing time is UTC+8, so if it's 13:50 Beijing time, that's 05:50 UTC, which would give `2026-04-13-05`. But the manual test created `2026-04-13-13.jsonl`. I'm confused about the timezone handling. Let me just send a new message and see if the hook actually writes to the ephemeral file.","thinkingSignature":"de628154af421e1d9a0750d6c078039a708c5ff159d153ffe60e5477efd4fa2a"},{"type":"text","text":"我发一条消息测试 hook 是否真的在写：\n\n这是测试消息。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":95463,"output":474,"