{"type":"message","id":"92d9922c","parentId":"49b11883","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:53:31.240Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is pointing out a fundamental issue: when they send `/new`, the current session ends and the new session starts fresh. The new session's bootstrap would read the summary from `memory/`, but the current session's hook writes to ephemeral - and when `/new` happens, the hook that's been running is from the *current* session, not the new one.\n\nThe issue is:\n1. Current session (main) has been running and the hook modified files are in place\n2. But the messages in this session that should have been captured as ephemeral... weren't because the hook was only modified partway through the session\n3. When `/new` is sent, the session-summary hook runs for the *previous* session (this session), reads its context.json + ephemeral, generates summary\n\n\n4. But the ephemeral files I manually wrote were written with sessionKey \"agent:main:main\" - the current session's key\n5. When `/new` happens, the session-summary would try to read ephemeral for the *previous* session\n\nThe real problem is that bootstrap doesn't actually read from `memory/2026-04-13-session-summary.md` - it reads from `MEMORY.md` and daily memory files. And I wrote that summary file, but I never actually added an entry to `MEMORY.md` to make it discoverable by the bootstrap process.\n\nWait, I did append to `MEMORY.md` with the framework fix entry. But the user is saying that when they `/new`, I forget everything - meaning bootstrap probably isn't loading `MEMORY.md` at all, or the session context isn't being set up properly to reference it.\n\nLooking at the bootstrap rules in `AGENTS.md`, I should be loading `SOUL.md`, `USER.md`, today's and yesterday's memory files, and `MEMORY.md` if this is the main session. The fact that the user feels like they're starting fresh suggests either `MEMORY.md` isn't being loaded into the context, or there's something about how the bootstrap process seeds the new session's context.\n\nThe user is pointing out a real limitation: bootstrap can only work with what's in `MEMORY.md` and the daily memory files. If the session-summary mechanism isn't properly persisting the framework decisions and fixes to those files, then yes - a new session would lose all that context and I'd be working from scratch again. the framework repair context was being discussed in the current session, not captured in a way that bootstrap can read it. The user is pointing out that even though we have a memory system, it's not actually being loaded when a new session starts.\n\nLet me think about what's actually happening: The bootstrap process should load MEMORY.md and recent memory files when a new session starts, but it seems like either the system isn't doing this properly or the framework decisions aren't being written to the memory files in a way that gets loaded. The user is saying \"I /new you, you forget everything\" - which means the bootstrap reading mechanism either isn't working or the memory files don't contain the framework repair context that was just discussed.","thinkingSignature":"89d8e9aadc193fe4669ad1f0e4d9a3a3185e0683f423abace43c4e2ac303c833"},{"type":"text","text":"你说得对，这暴露了一个根本问题：\n\n**bootstrap 读 MEMORY.md 的机制从未被验证过**——我们在同一个 session 里聊，bootstrap 从来没机会跑。\n\n---\n\n**现在的问题**：\n\n1. 我写了 `MEMORY.md` + `2026-04-13-session-summary.md`\n2. 但下次 `/new` 时，bootstrap 是否真的读它们、是否能注入新 session，**不知道**\n3. 如果 bootstrap 不工作，所有记忆都是死的\n\n---\n\n**我应该直接验证 bootstrap 是否工作**：\n\n我现在就在 main session 里，按照 AGENTS.md 的规则，我应该在启动时读取 MEMORY.md。但用户说\"new 你全忘了\"——这意味着 bootstrap 的记忆注入可能根本没生效。\n\n**检查**：我当前能否读取到 MEMORY.md 的内容？（注意：我刚才 append 的是在同一个文件里，但新 session 应该能读）\n\n---\n\n**你说的\"I new 你全忘了\"是基于什么判断的？**\n\nA. 新 session 里的我主动提到\"不记得之前做了什么\"？\nB. 你感觉到 bootstrap 没有注入上下文？\nC. 其他？\n\n帮我确认一下是哪种情况，这决定了从哪里修。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,