{"type":"message","id":"b343d798","parentId":"9ea2880f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:55:00.062Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is making a very sharp point. They're saying: \"You don't remember in this dialog either. What if you also don't remember when /new?\"\n\nThis is a fundamental concern. Let me think about what they mean:\n\n1. In the current session, I've been appending to memory files - but those writes happened because I used the `exec` tool to write files directly. The hook system (auto-score-classify) was supposed to write to ephemeral/, but that only captures NEW messages going forward.\n\n2. The problem is: in THIS session, the hook already ran for every message I received. But looking at the ephemeral file, it only has the 5 pre-written entries from the test file I manually created. \n\n3. That means my manual file write to the ephemeral file wasn't captured by the hook at all - it went straight to the file without triggering the hook's filtering logic.\n\n4. The real question is whether bootstrap actually reads from the session-summary file when a new session starts, and whether it injects that content into the new session's context. I haven't verified this works.\n\n5. The user is pointing out that even if I write to memory during this session, if bootstrap doesn't actually read and inject those memories when /new is triggered, then the memory system is fundamentally broken.\n\nSo the core issue is whether bootstrap is actually doing its job when /new is called, or if those memory files just sit there unread.\n\nI should verify the bootstrap mechanism to see if it's properly configured to load session-summary.md files at startup.","thinkingSignature":"93f4becd87484bbc11544006fbdd52a12b15c0c8e641a336bc7a7e2b2f4b1156"},{"type":"text","text":"对，这正好是刚才评审的结论。\n\n**session-summary + bootstrap 链路从未验证过**。我在这个 session 里写的 memory 文件，下个 session 能不能被 bootstrap 读到，取决于 bootstrap 的具体实现。\n\n---\n\n让我现在就检查 bootstrap 读取了什么：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0tzay2oy8y74_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn 'bootstrap\\|MEMORY.md\\|memory/.*.md\\|session-summary' ~/.openclaw/hooks/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v '.pyc' | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":432,"cacheRead":114420,"cacheWrite":171,"totalTokens":115077,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.0005184,"cacheRead":0.006865199999999999,"cacheWrite":0.000064125,"total":0.007463924999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776059680360,"responseId":"062bb81f03f052a057262fab70c5de33"}}
