{"type":"message","id":"f810b980","parentId":"d8618d8f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:55:23.451Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see! There's a `self-improvement` hook that fires on `agent:bootstrap` events. This hook injects a reminder during bootstrap. But it doesn't seem to inject MEMORY.md content directly - it pushes a bootstrap file that reminds the agent to evaluate learnings.\n\nBut the important question is: where does bootstrap actually read MEMORY.md and session summaries? Let me look at how bootstrap works. The AGENTS.md says:\n\n\"Read session context: look for `~/.openclaw/sessions/main@*/context.json`\"\n\nBut it also says \"Read the most recent session summary: scan `memory/` for files with `<!-- summary-only -->`, pick the latest by filename date, extract `## 主题`, `## 关键决策`, `## 待跟进` sections.\"\n \nWait, I'm realizing AGENTS.md defines the bootstrap process as reading SOUL.md, USER.md, today's memory files, MEMORY.md for main sessions, and session context - but these are file reads the LLM does at startup, not something the system injects. So if the system doesn't actually inject memory files and the LLM doesn't read them proactively either, then memory never gets loaded into context.\n\nThe user is pointing out that bootstrap probably isn't actually reading those memory files - the AGENTS.md rules might just be describing what should happen rather than what the system actually does. If that's true, then even if I write to memory files, they won't affect new sessions. The user seems to already know the answer to this based on their earlier testing.","thinkingSignature":"362653f8ba1479c81a9c65880cbaebe3fa627b824f12a397af1aa43383fd5202"},{"type":"text","text":"\n找到了：\n\n- `session-summary` hook 写 `memory/*.md`\n- `self-improvement` hook 只在 bootstrap 时 inject 一个\"evaluate learnings\"的提醒\n- **AGENTS.md 里写的是\"Read session summary\"，但这是给 LLM 的指令，不是系统注入**\n\n**问题是**：bootstrap 时，系统有没有把 `memory/*.md` 或 session-summary