{"type":"message","id":"f46aecdd","parentId":"2844a5f1","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:55:45.626Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"context.json only has the last message's classification and scoring. There's no bootstrap content injected here.\n\nThe user is absolutely right. The session context doesn't contain any memory file content. The AGENTS.md says \"Read session summary: scan memory/ for files with `<!-- summary-only -->`\" - but this is a directive for the LLM to READ those files itself, not for the system to inject them.\n\nSo the bootstrap \"reads\" memory files means the LLM reads them as part of its startup process. But in this session, the LLM was given a prompt that included \"Read SOUL.md, USER.md, memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md (today + yesterday)\" at startup. \n\nThe user might not have manually configured this bootstrap behavior, or the system might not be triggering it at all. Looking at the evidence: my workspace files ARE populated in the prompt, but there's no trace of memory file reads in the actual context that's been sent. This suggests the AGENTS.md directive to \"scan memory/ for files\" isn't being executed as an automatic system behavior - it's just an instruction that sits there.\n\nSo if the LLM only reads memory files when explicitly instructed, but new sessions never trigger that bootstrap instruction, then memory files are genuinely inert. The user is right to flag this. The real fix isn't adding more memory infrastructure - it's making sure the system actually reads those memory files at session start.","thinkingSignature":"13b73a87e9c491fd00e75d63db64984b3a8ec0aba02df7936480e321e6abce30"},{"type":"text","text":"**你说对了**。context.json 里只有 classification/scoring，没有 memory 文件内容。\n\nAGENTS.md 里写的是\"scan memory/ for files\"——这是给 LLM 的**指令**，不是系统的**注入动作**。系统只注入了 workspace 文件（SOUL.md、AGENTS.md 等），memory 文件从来没被注入过。\n\n---\n\n**bootstrap 是否真的按 AGENTS.md 指令读取 memory？**\n\n证据：\n- context.json 里没有 memory 内容\n- 我在这个 session 里写了 memory，但系统没有显示它读到了\n\n**结论**：AGENTS.md 的 bootstrap 指令可能根本没有被系统执行，它只是写在文件里的规则。\n\n---\n\n**你说的是对的**：new 的时候系统不注入 memory，LLM 也不一定主动读。**记忆系统是死的**。\n\n**最简单的修法**：让 bootstrap 在启动时，把 MEMORY.md 的内容作为 system prompt 的一部分注入进去。\n\n要修这个吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":98804,"output":478,"cacheRead":18037,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117319,"cost":{"input":0.0296412,"output":0.0005736,"cacheRead":0.0010822199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03129702}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776059723572,"responseId":"062bb84a3e47fc4930982c04e2cefb99"}}
