{"type":"message","id":"8fbfb770","parentId":"d43fbd05","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:59:58.779Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hnpdrmwwny3d_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"4: * Injects a reminder to evaluate learnings during agent bootstrap.\n5: * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n34:  // Only handle agent:bootstrap events\n35:  if (event.type !== 'agent' || event.action !== 'bootstrap') {\n44:  // Inject the reminder as a virtual bootstrap file\n45:  // Check that bootstrapFiles is an array before pushing\n46:  if (Array.isArray(event.context.bootstrapFiles)) {\n47:    event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":59,"aggregated":"4: * Injects a reminder to evaluate learnings during agent bootstrap.\n5: * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n34:  // Only handle agent:bootstrap events\n35:  if (event.type !== 'agent' || event.action !== 'bootstrap') {\n44:  // Inject the reminder as a virtual bootstrap file\n45:  // Check that bootstrapFiles is an array before pushing\n46:  if (Array.isArray(event.context.bootstrapFiles)) {\n47:    event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776059998770}}
{"type":"message","id":"970bd9a7","parentId":"8fbfb770","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:00:10.725Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The self-improvement hook (`handler.js`) pushes a bootstrap file into `event.context.bootstrapFiles`. This is the system-level bootstrap injection mechanism! Files pushed into `bootstrapFiles` are injected into the session.\n\nSo the mechanism exists. The question is: does MEMORY.md get pushed into `bootstrapFiles` somewhere?\n\nLet me search for where bootstrapFiles is populated, and whether MEMORY.md is among the files that get injected.\n\nActually, looking at the hook - it just pushes a self-improvement reminder file. It's not injecting MEMORY.md.\n\nThe solution is simple: create a hook (or modify the existing self-improving hook) that pushes MEMORY.md content into `bootstrapFiles`.Or even simpler: modify the self-improving hook's handler to also read and inject MEMORY.md.\n\n\nNow I need to examine what the current self-improving hook is doing so I can modify it to handle MEMORY.md injection.","thinkingSignature":"a33bad85a205a247bea2c562f38fdf8eaed2a985749701b3bb73c5d310b0693c"},{"type":"text","text":"找到了。`bootstrapFiles` 是系统级别的注入机制——往里面 push 文件，新 session 就会自动注入。\n\nself-improving hook 已经有这个能力，它往 bootstrapFiles 写了一个\"evaluate learnings\"提醒。\n\n**修法**：在这个 hook 里加一行，把 MEMORY.md 也推进 bootstrapFiles：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zx7z5q134ex9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/handler.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":99785,"output":281,"cacheRead":18037,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":118103,"cost":{"input":0.0299355,"output":0.0003372,"cacheRead":0.0010822199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03135492}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776059998785,"responseId":"062bb95ed26cb5dec52c8dfeba15e44f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"fe9a994a","parentId":"970bd9a7","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:00:10.839Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zx7z5q134ex9_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * Self-Improvement Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * Injects a reminder to evaluate learnings during agent bootstrap.\n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n */\n\nconst REMINDER_CONTENT = `\n## Self-Improvement Reminder\n\nAfter completing tasks, evaluate if any learnings should be captured:\n\n**Log when:**\n- User corrects you → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- Command/operation fails → \\`.learnings/ERRORS.md\\`\n- User wants missing capability → \\`.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md\\`\n- You discover your knowledge was wrong → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- You find a better approach → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n\n**Promote when pattern is proven:**\n- Behavioral patterns → \\`SOUL.md\\`\n- Workflow improvements → \\`AGENTS.md\\`\n- Tool gotchas → \\`TOOLS.md\\`\n\nKeep entries simple: date, title, what happened, what to do differently.\n`.trim();\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  // Safety checks for event structure\n  if (!event || typeof event !== 'object') {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Only handle agent:bootstrap events\n  if (event.type !== 'agent' || event.action !== 'bootstrap') {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Safety check for context\n  if (!event.context || typeof event.context !== 'object') {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Inject the reminder as a virtual bootstrap file\n  // Check that bootstrapFiles is an array before pushing\n  if (Array.isArray(event.context.bootstrapFiles)) {\n    event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n      path: 'SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER.md',\n      content: REMINDER_CONTENT,\n      virtual: true,\n    });\n  }\n};\n\nmodule.exports = handler;\nmodule.exports.default = handler;"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":63,"aggregated":"/**\n * Self-Improvement Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * Injects a reminder to evaluate learnings during agent bootstrap.\n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n */\n\nconst REMINDER_CONTENT = `\n## Self-Improvement Reminder\n\nAfter completing tasks, evaluate if any learnings should be captured:\n\n**Log when:**\n- User corrects you → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- Command/operation fails → \\`.learnings/ERRORS.md\\`\n- User wants missing capability → \\`.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md\\`\n- You discover your knowledge was wrong → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- You find a better approach → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n\n**Promote when pattern is proven:**\n- Behavioral patterns → \\`SOUL.md\\`\n- Workflow improvements → \\`AGENTS.md\\`\n- Tool gotchas → \\`TOOLS.md\\`\n\nKeep entries simple: date, title, what happened, what to do differently.\n`.trim();\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  // Safety checks for event structure\n  if (!event || typeof event !== 'object') {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Only handle agent:bootstrap events\n  if (event.type !== 'agent' || event.action !== 'bootstrap') {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Safety check for context\n  if (!event.context || typeof event.context !== 'object') {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Inject the reminder as a virtual bootstrap file\n  // Check that bootstrapFiles is an array before pushing\n  if (Array.isArray(event.context.bootstrapFiles)) {\n    event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n      path: 'SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER.md',\n      content: REMINDER_CONTENT,\n      virtual: true,\n    });\n  }\n};\n\nmodule.exports = handler;\nmodule.exports.default = handler;","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776060010827}}
{"type":"message","id":"6b952b30","parentId":"fe9a994a","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:00:36.875Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the self-improvement hook. It injects a SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER.md virtual file into bootstrapFiles.\n\nI need to also inject MEMORY.md and the session summary files. Let me modify this hook to also read MEMORY.md and the latest session summary files, and push them into bootstrapFiles.\n\nI need to be careful about:\n1. Reading the filesystem (async fs operations)\n2. Pushing multiple files\n3. Not breaking the existing reminder injection","thinkingSignature":"fcc7ae4786060f409d5f31466d99e512d27183c0c5c5b4dd888a131853738f1a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uo6p4uq501pq_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"/**\n * Self-Improvement Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * Injects:\n * 1. Self-improvement reminder\n * 2. MEMORY.md content (long-term memory)\n * 3. Latest session summaries (recent context)\n * \n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n */\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport os from \"node:os\";\n\nconst MEMORY_ROOT = path.join(\n  process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR || path.join(os.homedir(), \".openclaw\", \"workspace\"),\n  \"memory\"\n);\n\nconst SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER = `\n## Self-Improvement Reminder\n\nAfter completing tasks, evaluate if any learnings should be captured:\n\n**Log when:**\n- User corrects you → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- Command/operation fails → \\`.learnings/ERRORS.md\\`\n- User wants missing capability → \\`.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md\\`\n- You discover your knowledge was wrong → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- You find a better approach → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n\n**Promote when pattern is proven:**\n- Behavioral patterns → \\`SOUL.md\\`\n- Workflow improvements → \\`AGENTS.md\\`\n- Tool gotchas → \\`TOOLS.md\\`\n\nKeep entries simple: date, title, what happened, what to do differently.\n`.trim();\n\n// Read latest session summaries from memory/\nasync function getRecentSummaries() {\n  /** @type {string[]} */\n  const summaries = [];\n  try {\n    const files = await fs.promises.readdir(MEMORY_ROOT);\n    // Get .md files that contain \"summary\" or date pattern (most recent 3)\n    const summaryFiles = files\n      .filter(f => (f.includes('summary') || f.match(/\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}/)) && f.endsWith('.md'))\n      .filter(f => !f.startsWith('MEMORY'))\n      .sort()\n      .reverse()\n      .slice(0, 3);\n    \n    for (const file of summaryFiles) {\n      try {\n        const content = await fs.promises.readFile(path.join(MEMORY_ROOT, file), 'utf-8');\n        // Skip summary-only marked files if they're too long (>2000 chars)\n        if (content.includes('<!-- summary-only -->') && content.length < 2000) {\n          summaries.push({ path: file, content });\n        } else if (!content.includes('<!-- summary-only -->')) {\n          summaries.push({ path: file, content: content.slice(0, 1000) });\n        }\n      } catch { /* skip */ }\n    }\n  } catch { /* memory dir may not exist */ }\n  return summaries;\n}\n\n// Read MEMORY.md\nasync function getMemoryIndex() {\n  try {\n    const content = await fs.promises.readFile(path.join(process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR || path.join(os.homedir(), '.openclaw/workspace'), 'MEMORY.md'), 'utf-8');\n    return content.slice(0, 2000);\n  } catch { return null; }\n}\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  // Safety checks\n  if (!event || typeof event !== 'object') return;\n  if (event.type !== 'agent' || event.action !== 'bootstrap') return;\n  if (!event.context || typeof event.context !== 'object') return;\n  if (!Array.isArray(event.context.bootstrapFiles)) return;\n\n  // 1. Self-improvement reminder (always inject)\n  event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n    path: 'SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER.md',\n    content: SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER,\n    virtual: true,\n  });\n\n  // 2. MEMORY.md (long-term memory index)\n  const memoryContent = await getMemoryIndex();\n  if (memoryContent) {\n    event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n      path: 'MEMORY.md',\n      content: memoryContent,\n      virtual: true,\n    });\n  }\n\n  // 3. Recent session summaries\n  const summaries = await getRecentSummaries();\n  for (const summary of summaries) {\n    event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n      path: `memory/${summary.path}`,\n      content: summary.content,\n      virtual: true,\n    });\n  }\n};\n\nexport default handler;\nmodule.exports = handler;\nmodule.exports.default = handler;\n","path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/handler.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":100475,"output":1083,"cacheRead":18037,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":119595,"cost":{"input":0.0301425,"output":0.0012996,"cacheRead":0.0010822199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03252432}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776060010846,"responseId":"062bb96a2400a9447947600070a91dfc"}}
