{"type":"message","id":"d47d83bb","parentId":"d41bf4e3","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:13:59.982Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"As I suspected - the v8 version is running on 3104, not the workspace version. The v8 version still has the numpy serialization bug. When I killed 442 earlier and started the workspace version, the workspace version was killed when the gateway restarted (which might have triggered the old systemd services). Now the v8 version is back on 3104 with the old numpy bug.\n\nI need to:\n1. Kill the v8 version on 3104\n2. Start the workspace version\n\nBut the problem is the workspace version runs in foreground and doesn't daemonize properly. Let me start it properly as a background process.\n\nActually, looking at the current situation - the v8 version is the one that was running when gateway restarted. \n\nThe gateway restart might have triggered the old hooks to reload, or possibly the cron job that runs wiki-auto-learn periodically could have also restarted the old v8 process. Either way, the workspace version that should be running on 3104 got replaced by the v8 version, which still has the numpy bug causing the Internal Server Error. The workspace version must have gotten killed at some point, and then the systemd service restarted the old v8 version automatically since it was configured to restart. I need to kill the old v8 instance and get the workspace version running on 3104 instead, though I'll need to set it up properly as a background process since it doesn't daemonize on its own.","thinkingSignature":"102101f5e60f5baa1677585e5b586c74709ffcab76c60300dd77b6a7d44bffc4"},{"type":"text","text":"3104 又跑回了 v8 旧版（numpy bug）。systemd 在 gateway 重启后自动拉起了旧版。\n\n重新修复：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uyk7hkzqotiq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"kill 57472 && sleep 1 && echo \"killed\"; bash /tmp/run_ws.sh && sleep 5 && lsof -i :3104"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model"