{"type":"message","id":"b8663aeb","parentId":"30de95b6","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:16:16.083Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The service file runs from `/home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier` with `Restart=always`. So when the gateway restarts, this service restarts and grabs port 3104.I need to change the `Restart=always` to `Restart=no` or remove the `Restart=` line. But I need elevated permissions.Wait, the process is running as user `ai`, but the service file modification requires root. However, I could modify the running behavior differently...Actually, the service is running as `User=ai`, so if I can edit the service file as `ai`, that would work. But it's in `/etc/systemd/system/` which requires root.Let me think of another approach: since the workspace version is already on 3104 (pid 60341), and the scene-classifier.service keeps restarting and getting killed (because it fails to bind - EADDRINUSE), it will eventually give up after some retries.Or I could modify the v8 scene-classifier's api_server.py to listen on a different port, so it doesn't conflict.Or... actually, the simplest fix: change the workspace version to also use the same startup mechanism, and ensure it starts BEFORE the scene-classifier.service starts.But I don't have root access to modify systemd services.Let me think... The workspace version of the scene-classifier was started manually with our `/tmp/run_ws.sh` script. It's running as pid 60341. The systemd service keeps trying to restart and failing because the port is in use. Eventually it will stop retrying... Actually with `Restart=always` it will keep trying forever.Wait, I notice something: the service has `RestartSec=5` but the workspace version (60341) is still running. So the service keeps getting killed or failing to start. I can modify the ExecStart to point to the correct workspace version instead, or change the port. But again, I need root for /etc/systemd/system/.Actually wait - the service file is owned by root, but the `User=ai` means it runs as `ai` user. I can't modify the service file without root. But I can create a new service file in a user-level location... Actually no, user-level systemd services work differently.\n\nI could create a user-level systemd service instead, but the simplest approach is probably to just modify the v8 scene-classifier api_server.py to bind to a different port like 3105, or change its `RestartSec` to something longer. Since I don't have root access to systemctl, the most practical solution is to accept that the workspace version will keep getting knocked off whenever systemd retries the service - the race condition means the workspace version usually wins anyway.","thinkingSignature":"6cfe570b8d88eb335725cfbe69c6e9ddde040547a4df5a12f312718063c636f9"},{"type":"text","text":"**问题根源**：scene-classifier.service 是 v8 版本，Restart=always，每次 gateway 重启都尝试抢 3104。\n\n**无法停掉**（没有 root 权限），但好消息是 workspace 版本已经在跑了（60341），会一直赢因为 v8 版本绑不上（端口被占）。\n\n**现在能做的**：把 v8 scene-classifier 改成不抢占 3104。最简单的方法——改 v8 版本的监听端口：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v1db3m3i1rdh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n '3104\\|port' /home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier/api_server.py | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":111373,"output":699,"cacheRead":18037,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":130109,"cost":{"input":0.0334119,"output":0.0008388,"cacheRead":0.0010822199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.035332920000000004}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776060946894,"responseId":"062bbd13ef38c7af61c411df9878d2df"}}
