{"type":"message","id":"28af43b3","parentId":"7a5dbf7e","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:27:13.474Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now SOUL.md has an explicit startup check. This is the first thing that will be injected into my context at the start of every session.\n\nBut wait - will SOUL.md be re-injected on /new? Yes, SOUL.md is a workspace file, and workspace files are injected at bootstrap. So when /new happens, SOUL.md gets re-injected, and the first thing in it is this startup check.\n\nHowever, there's still a question: does the LLM actually follow the instructions in SOUL.md? The system injects SOUL.md as context, but the LLM needs to actually read and obey it. This is still a \"trust the LLM will follow the rule\" mechanism, not a system-level enforcement.\n \nThe real safeguards are now layered throughout: the self-improving hook injects MEMORY.md at startup, AGENTS.md has the bootstrap reading rule, and SOUL.md now has this explicit check. If any one of these works, I'll see the memory. The user is protected as long as at least one of these mechanisms functions.","thinkingSignature":"51e564e8e6b24f514d4635734876bde98b676dfd8a8b71b1848e444418e0b76a"},{"type":"text","text":"**保底已加**。SOUL.md 是 workspace 文件里最优先注入的，现在它第一条是：\n\n```\n若这是 /new 后首次回复：\n1. 读取 memory/MEMORY.md，检查是否有 \"2026-04-13\"\n2. 若有，摘要陈述\n```\n\n**三层保底**：\n\n| 层 | 机制 | 注入方式 |\n|----|------|----------|\n| 1 | self-improving hook | 系统自动 push 到 bootstrapFiles |\n| 2 | SOUL.md 启动检查 | workspace 文件注入，LLM 第一个看到 |\n| 3 | AGENTS.md bootstrap 规则 | 写在文件里的 LLM 指令 |\n\n三层里只要有一层生效，记忆就能传递。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":24784,"output":375,"cacheRead":18037,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43196,"cost":{"input":0.0074351999999999994,"output":0.00045,"cacheRead":0.0010822199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00896742}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776061617972,"responseId":"062bbfb15247c8b34bb1e5c57305890b"}}
