{"type":"message","id":"c888dff3","parentId":"10e87ce5","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:27:54.422Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There are issues:\n\n1. **3104 Unauthorized** - This is the gateway acting as the 3104 endpoint (gateway has a built-in route for /classify that requires auth), not the workspace scene-classifier. The workspace scene-classifier is not running.\n\n2. **openclaw-gateway on port 3104** - The gateway itself (pid 64417) is listening on 3104, NOT the workspace scene-classifier. The workspace api_server is NOT running.\n\n3. **3101 and 3102 return HTML** - This means they're not the context-api or gateway health endpoints - likely the routes have changed or these are returning the default HTML response.\n\n\n4. The workspace scene-classifier (pid 61342) is sitting idle on port 3105, completely unused while the gateway has taken over 3104, and 3103 is only returning the score without a scene classification. I need to restart the workspace service to reclaim 3104 and fix the authentication issue.","thinkingSignature":"a8b3643af3bb13aaebde6790871dfe20bf3a60c52d741127057a5c57a7bd0944"},{"type":"text","text":"**发现问题**：\n\n- 3104 上跑的是 **gateway 自己**（pid 64417），不是 workspace scene-classifier\n- workspace scene-classifier 跑在 **3105**（没用上）\n- 3104 返回 \"Unauthorized\"，gateway 的内置认证拦截了\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_shh8ckaqdfso_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux | grep 'api_server' | grep -v grep"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":25664,"output":300,"cacheRead":18037,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44001,"cost":{"input":0.0076992,"output":0.00035999999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0010822199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009141419999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776061665000,"responseId":"062bbfdff287442af7873e5572625adb"}}
