{"type":"message","id":"71193ee6","parentId":"7d33eba8","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:28:35.974Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gateway is still on 3104. When I kill 61342 and start workspace, gateway is already on 3104 so workspace gets 3105. But now workspace isn't even starting because the old process (that was killed) is gone and there's nothing on 3105 anymore.\n\nLet me check the workspace log to see why it didn't start.Wait, the `bash /tmp/run_ws.sh` output shows PID: 65534, but that was the `echo \"PID: $!\"` from the script. The actual python server would be a child of that shell. Let me check if it's running.\n\nActually, I think the issue is that `run_ws.sh` starts the server in the background and immediately returns. \n\nThe python process might not have started at all. Let me check the log and see what's happening.","thinkingSignature":"287cbec4bbf65a42b6ac6fb1510d595275512ce638a3c2376621ff7ceacbafe3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g57za46puij4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /tmp/sc_ws.log 2>/dev/null | tail -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":26848,"output":208,"cacheRead":18037,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45093,"cost":{"input":0.0080544,"output":0.0002496,"cacheRead":0.0010822199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009386219999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776061706549,"responseId":"062bc00a95736d3983b49f66f0d33d4f"}}
