{"type":"message","id":"f21502bb","parentId":"f052960b","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:29:44.911Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Process 65569 is the V8 version of scene-classifier on port 3105. So:3104: gateway (workspace scene-classifier is NOT running, v8 is on 3105)And earlier when I tested 3105, it returned Internal Server Error. The v8 version on 3105 has the numpy bug (since we changed the v8 version to port 3105 to avoid competing, but we didn't fix the numpy bug in the v8 version - we only deployed the fix in the workspace version).\n\nSo the current situation is:- 3104: gateway- 3105: v8 scene-classifier (Internal Server Error due to numpy bug)And the workspace scene-classifier (the fixed version) is not running at all.The fix I did earlier was to kill the old v8 process on 3104 and start the workspace version on 3104. But then gateway restarted and took 3104 again, and then when I restarted workspace it fell back to... wait let me trace through what actually happened.\n\nLooking at the earlier sequence:\n1. scene-classifier.service (v8) was on 3104\n2. We killed it, started workspace with run_ws.sh\n3. Gateway restarted (from our earlier restart command) and took 3104\n4. run_ws.sh tried to start workspace on 3104 but gateway was there, so it got 3105 (or failed)\n\nActually, looking at the lsof data from the comprehensive check - at that point:\n- 61342 was on 3105 (v8 version)\n- gateway was on 3104\n- 57453 was v8 scorer on 3103\n\nAnd when I killed 61342 and ran run_ws.sh, the new process got 3105 (65569, which is v8). So the workspace version isn't running at all!\n\nThe root problem is that run_ws.sh runs `python3 api_server.py` from the workspace directory, but the process that actually started was the v8 version instead. When I checked the cwd for 65569, it showed the v8 directory, not workspace - so either run_ws.sh was somehow running the wrong script, or the workspace version died and got replaced.\n\nActually, looking at the lsof output again, 65569 is clearly the v8 version (v8 directory), not workspace. So workspace version is NOT running. The v8 version on 3105 gives Internal Server Error because it has the numpy bug.\n\nSo the workspace scene-classifier (which has the fixed numpy serialization) is not running at all. I need to fix this.\n\nMy approach: kill 65569, then manually start the workspace version on 3104 by modifying its api_server.py to use a different port first, or use a startup script that ensures it binds to 3104 before gateway does.\n\nActually, I should just update the run_ws.sh script to specify port 3104 explicitly, then stop the v8 version, and restart with the corrected script.","thinkingSignature":"702b61696dc8afafd077d5dad0605a528032f3eb5c1705f08622713a1ba01532"},{"type":"text","text":"**根因找到了**：workspace scene-classifier（修复版）根本没在跑。3105 上的是 v8 版本（有 numpy bug）。\n\n进程 65569（v8）占了 3105，workspace 版本在 8080 启动失败。\n\n**修复**：杀掉 v8，重启 workspace 版本：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ybsj7sgia0d9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"kill 65569 2>/dev/null\nsleep 2\n# 直接在 workspace 目录启动，强制 3104\ncd /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/skills/scene-classifier && python3 api_server.py >> /tmp/sc_ws.log 2>&1 &\necho \"PID: $!\"\nsleep 6\nlsof -i :3104 2>/dev/null | tail -2"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":29214,"output":791,"cacheRead":18037,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48042,"cost":{"input":0.0087642,"output":0.0009492,"cacheRead":0.0010822199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01079562}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776061761528,"responseId":"062bc0413181171ee9614ee36b00f614"}}
