{"type":"message","id":"9fdb6742","parentId":"0b9f3dc1","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:30:32.926Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'll add a fallback port mechanism. If 3104 is in use, use 3108 (or some other port). But I also need to update the gateway configuration to use the new port, or just make the scene-classifier use 3104 only.Actually, the simplest approach: modify the api_server.py to try 3104 first, and if that fails, fall back to 3108. Then update the hook to use 3108.Wait, but the hook is hardcoded to use 3104. And the gateway uses 3104 as well.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The gateway is configured to proxy /classify to port 3104. \n\nIf I change the scene-classifier to run on 3108 and update the gateway config to proxy to 3108 instead, that should work. Let me check what the gateway configuration looks like.","thinkingSignature":"37b889054b23f16a74c6561bb3ba99935069f0562425309bbc68fd841c9cc6bc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1isr3uz6rr1q_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n '3104\\|classify' ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":31238,"output":231,"cacheRead":18037,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49506,"cost":{"input":0.0093714,"output":0.00027719999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0010822199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01073082}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776061824314,"responseId":"062bc07fed7ab5dfd28441f3e87ab5bc"}}
