{"type":"message","id":"b5daddc6","parentId":"d994a265","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:30:44.631Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The grep result shows that 3104 only appears in the auto-score-classify section (line 321), not as a general gateway classification endpoint. So the gateway doesn't have a built-in /classify route that proxies to 3104 - the \"Unauthorized\" response must be coming from somewhere else in the gateway.\n\nWait, but when I curled 3104 and got \"Unauthorized\" - what exactly is running on port 3104? It's the gateway (pid 64417). And when I curled 3104/classify, the gateway returned \"Unauthorized\". So the gateway must have a built-in route for /classify that requires auth.\n\nBut the auto-score-classify hook in the gateway config (line 321) probably tells the gateway to call the hook on certain messages, which then calls port 3104. \n\nSo the issue is that gateway's built-in /classify endpoint is separate from the hook. I should just modify the workspace api_server.py to use 3108 as a fallback when 3104 is unavailable, and update the hook to call 3108 instead. Though I need to be careful about which version of the workspace api_server.py actually needs this fix.","thinkingSignature":"0a85da8a941a6d0b83536626918023bd34f0b1b11cfaf4262a227ae1f8e10471"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q8kna3pk0ecy_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/skills/scene-classifier/api_server.py","edits":[{"newText":"if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    import socket\n    port = 3104\n    for p in [3104, 3108, 3109]:\n        try:\n            s = socket.socket()\n            s.bind(('0.0.0.0', p))\n            s.close()\n            port = p\n            break\n        except OSError:\n            continue\n    print(f\"Scene Classifier API v2.0 starting on port {port}...\")\n    uvicorn.run(app, host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=port)","oldText":"if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    print(\"Scene Classifier API v