{"type":"message","id":"c421fb82","parentId":"0fd999dc","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:34:55.486Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, the issue is that the workspace scene-classifier api_server.py hardcodes 3104 as the port (which I modified to try multiple ports). But the v8 version is the one that keeps getting systemd to restart. The workspace version is what we want.\n\nLet me just kill everything and restart fresh. The key issue is:\n1. v8 scene-classifier on 3105 (keep it, doesn't conflict with anything)2. workspace scene-classifier - we need this on 3108/3109/etc\n\nBut actually - looking at the situation:- The gateway's built-in scene-classifier (when no external one is available)- vs the workspace one\n\nWait, the gateway is on 3104. The 3104 test was returning \"Unauthorized\" which means the gateway IS actually intercepting the request (probably for auth). Let me check what the gateway does when a request comes to 3104.\n \nAh, I see - when I tested 3104 directly it showed \"Unauthorized\", but the hook makes internal calls that might bypass that auth check. So the gateway itself is functioning as the classifier on 3104, while the workspace version tried to bind there and failed. That explains why the gateway is returning responses - it's handling the classification internally rather than proxying to the workspace service.\n\nLet me just restart fresh and verify everything is actually working correctly now.","thinkingSignature":"cfb77bdd107452ad169d175f3663bcd97a13c0cb65ccf0825e11e5cc75cfbcb7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5uab4s9pghaw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"bash /tmp/run_ws3.sh && sleep 8 && ss -tlnp | grep -E '3104|3105|3108'"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":32485,"output":335,"cacheRead":18127,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50947,"cost":{"input":0.009745499999999999,"output":0.00040199999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0010876199999999999