{"type":"message","id":"b0c84330","parentId":"35f68a94","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:36:33.176Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway log is empty (only has the config warnings). The log file was probably overwritten when the gateway restarted.\n\nLet me just verify the overall status. The key things are:\n1. 3108 is working ✅\n2. Gateway is running ✅\n3. Hook code is updated to 3108 ✅\n4. The context.json not updating classification might be a display timing issue or the gateway not calling the hook on this particular message\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The context.json file was last modified at 06:33 UTC. The \"怎么样\" message was received at 14:33 CST (06:33 UTC). The fact that the messagePreview shows \"怎么样\" but classification=null could mean:\n\n\n- The hook's writeEphemeral ran successfully and didn't update context.json for classification since it's not stored there\n- The auto-score-classify hook might not actually update context.json with classification data at all\n\nLooking at the hook code, it fetches classification from 3104 (now 3108) and scoring from 3103, but the actual context.json update depends on what the gateway does with those results. The context.json structure I'm seeing is the session context format, so the classification and scoring data should be flowing through the hook, but maybe the gateway isn't persisting those results back to context.json in this case.\n\nLet me focus on the actual problem instead of chasing why one message didn't get classified. The gateway is running, 3108 is working, the hook code points to the right port, and 3103 is responding. I should test the full flow end-to-end rather than debugging this one message anomaly.","thinkingSignature":"773a8f7f7536f869b5aafdee9d3e4acac89b2951add23a1ef607fa67b8a70924"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lzjj7s1ykagn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /tmp/sc_ws.log 2>/dev/null | grep -E 'POST|200|error' | tail -5"}}],"a