{"type":"message","id":"a6bba3b3","parentId":"dabb02e7","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:44:55.172Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if there's anything that needs to be added or supplemented. Let me think about what's actually missing or could be improved.\n\nLooking at what's deployed:\n1. ✅ 3104 scene-classifier (workspace, port 3108) \n2. ✅ 3103 v8-scorer (port 3103)\n3. ✅ gateway (port 3104)\n4. ✅ auto-score-classify hook (captures meaningful messages)\n5. ✅ session-summary hook (but never triggered)\n6. ✅ self-improving hook (injects MEMORY.md on bootstrap)\n\n\n7. ✅ cron jobs (wiki-auto-learn, memory-keeper, memory-maintain)\n\nThe two hooks that handle ephemeral message capture and session summarization haven't been validated yet since they only trigger on /new. I'm also noticing that context.json writes classification as null, and while the hook successfully captured the \"记住我用的是 webchat\" message, it appears to be the only meaningful event recorded recently.\n\nLooking at what could strengthen this setup: the SOUL.md bootstrap mechanism is the main defense since we can't verify the hooks actually work, session-summary and bootstrap only trigger on /new creating a testing bottleneck, and ephemeral still has just that single entry. Beyond these, the 26 workspace skills are installed but mostly unused, there's no real monitoring beyond manual checks, and while bootstrapFiles could theoretically inject memories, there's no way to verify it's actually happening.\n\nThe most practical gap is probably clearer documentation of what each hook should do and when, plus better visibility into whether the memory system is functioning as intended.","thinkingSignature":"c6d49005e14e6f39b69798672e9df52acd1b1f746fb4ab0332458bcb6305c45c"},{"type":"text","text":"## 缺的东西\n\n### 1. session-summary 从未验证\nsession-summary hook 写了代码但从未触发过。ephemeral 里有1条记录，但没有被提炼成 entity。\n\n### 2. bootstrap 注入无法验证\nSOUL.md 加了启动规则保底，但新 session 启动时是否真的注入 MEMORY.md，没有确认。\n\n### 3. 没有监控\n3108 scene-classifier 如果再崩，gateway 重启时会一并拉起 v8 有 bug 的旧版，然后覆盖 3108。虽然改过 api_server.py 的端口检测逻辑，但并没有持久化保障。\n\n### 4. 端口漂移\n3108 是临时抢来的，systemd scene-classifier 随时可能抢回去。每次重启 gateway 都要手动检查。\n\n---\n\n## 最需要补充的一件实事\n\n**持久化 3108 的 scene-classifier**，不依赖手动启动：\n\n现在 scene-classifier 靠手动 bash 脚本跑，没有 systemd。可以在 cron 里加一个守护：\n```bash\n* * * * * pgrep -f \"scene-classifier.*api_server\" > /dev/null || bash /tmp/run_ws3.sh\n```\n\n每分钟检查一次，死了就拉起来。\n\n---\n\n**其他的**：记忆系统、cron 都已在跑，没有紧急需要补充的。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":587,"cacheRead":58225,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58812,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0.0007044,"cacheRead":0.0034934999999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004197899999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776062671913,"responseId":"062bc3cf3ead250c4a1096711e735342"}}
